VDs==\n* \u0399\u0399\u0399 F.I.C. Festival Internacional Da Can\u00e7\u00e3o 1968 Rio\n* 2004 \u2013 Athens 2004 Olympic Games\n\n==Marinella in Greek cinema==\nThe following table is a record of all instances of Marinella in films of Greek cinema, from the 1960 by 1966 with [[Stelios Kazantzidis]] and from 1967 by 1970 itself.<ref>Compilation album ''Ta Kinimatografika Tou Kazantzidi'' (Booklet), [[EMI]] (Greece): 37936924, 2006</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- \"\n! Year !! Movie title !! Director !! Songs\n|-\n|1960\n|\nKYRIA DIMARHOS <small>(Madame mayor)<ref>[http://www.tainiothiki.gr/v2/lang_en/filmography/view/1/1303/ Greek Film Archive (Film Museum) \u2013 MADAME MAYOR 1960]</ref></small>\n|\nRoviros Manthoulis\n|\n\"Gia 'mas pote min ximerosi\", \"Ziguala\", \"Allaxane ta pragmata\"\n|-\n|1962\n|\nKLAPSE, FTOHI MOU KARDIA <small>(Weep, my poor heart)<ref>[http://www.tainiothiki.gr/v2/lang_en/filmography/view/1/1182/ Greek Film Archive (Film Museum) \u2013 WEEP, MY POOR HEART 1962]</ref></small>\n|\nKostas Strantzalis\n|\n\"Fevgo me pikra sta xena\"\n|-\n|1965\n|\nPEXE, BOUZOUKI MOU GLYKO <small>(Play, my sweet bouzouki)<ref>[http://www.tainiothiki.gr/v2/lang_en/filmography/view/1/1842/ Greek Film Archive (Film Museum) \u2013 PLAY, MY SWEET BOUZOUKI 1965]</ref></small>\n|\nKostas Strantzalis\n|\n\"Fevgo me pikra sta xena\"\n|-\n|1965\n|\nAFISTE ME NA ZISO <small>(Let me live)<ref>[http://www.tainiothiki.gr/v2/lang_en/filmography/view/1/54/ Greek Film Archive (Film Museum) \u2013 LET ME LIVE 1965]</ref></small>\n|\nAndreas Katsimitsoulias\n|\n\"Emis mazi tha zisoume\"\n|-\n|1965\n|\nI ADISTAKTI <small>(The unhesitant)<ref>[http://www.tainiothiki.gr/v2/lang_en/filmography/view/1/31/ Greek Film Archive (Film Museum) \u2013 UNHESITANT (THE) 1965]</ref></small>\n|\nDinos Katsouridis\n|\n\"Pios dromos eine anihtos\"\n|-\n|1965\n|\nPRODOMENI <small>(Betrayed)<ref>[http://www.tainiothiki.gr/v2/lang_en/filmography/view/1/1930/ Greek Film Archive (Film Museum) \u2013 BETRAYED 1965]</ref></small>\n|\nChristos Kyriakopoulos\n|\n\"Mes stis agapis mas to tzaki\", \"Tora pou s' eho anagki\"\n|-\n|1965\n|\nTIMORIA <small>(Punishment)<ref>[http://www.tainiothiki.gr/v2/lang_en/filmography/view/1/2292/ Greek Film Archive (Film Museum) \u2013 PUNISHMENT 1965]</ref></small>\n|\nDinos Katsouridis\n|\n\"Na fygo, na fygo\", \"Prodomenes kardies\"\n|-\n|1965\n|\nI KATAFRONEMENI <small>(The scorned)<ref>[http://www.tainiothiki.gr/v2/lang_en/filmography/view/1/1108/ Greek Film Archive (Film Museum) \u2013 SCORNED (THE) 1965]</ref></small>\n|\nNikos Varveris\n|\n\"Orkizome stin antriki timi mou\"\n|-\n|1965\n|\nDEN MPOROUN NA MAS HORISOUN <small>(They can't keep us apart)<ref>[http://www.tainiothiki.gr/v2/lang_en/filmography/view/1/450/ Greek Film Archive (Film Museum) \u2013 THEY CAN\u2019T KEEP US APART 1965]</ref></small>\n|\nChristos Kyriakopoulos\n|\n\"Me to voria\"\n|-\n|1966\n|\nI AGGELI TIS AMARTIAS <small>(Angels of sin)<ref>[http://www.tainiothiki.gr/v2/lang_en/filmography/view/1/69/ Greek Film Archive (Film Museum) \u2013 ANGELS OF SIN 1966]</ref></small>\n|\nAndreas Katsimitsoulias\n|\n\"Na fygo, na fygo\"\n|-\n|1967\n|\nHARTORIHTRA <small>(The fortune teller)<ref>[http://www.tainiothiki.gr/v2/lang_en/filmography/view/1/374/ Greek Film Archive (Film Museum) \u2013 FORTUNE TELLER (THE) 1967]</ref></small>\n|\n[[Kostas Karagiannis]]\n|\n\"Dos' mou agapi\", \"Eime hartorihtra fina\"\n|-\n|1968\n|\nO PIO KALOS O MATHITIS <small>(The best student)<ref>[http://www.tainiothiki.gr/v2/lang_en/filmography/view/1/1853/ Greek Film Archive (Film Museum) \u2013 BEST STUDENT (THE) 1968]</ref></small>\n|\n[[Kostas Andritsos]]\n|\n\"Stalia \u2013 stalia\"\n|-\n|1968\n|\nGORGONES KE MAGKES <small>(Mermaids and tough guys)<ref>[http://www.tainiothiki.gr/v2/lang_en/filmography/view/1/927/ Greek Film Archive (Film Museum) \u2013 MERMAIDS AND TOUGH GUYS 1968]</ref></small>\n|\n[[Giannis Dalianidis]]\n|\n\"Anixe petra\", \"Anixe Petra (Mpate koritsia sto horo)\"\n|-\n|1969\n|\n[[Gymnoi sto dromo|GYMNI STO DROMO]] <small>(Naked in the street)<ref>[http://www.tainiothiki.gr/v2/lang_en/filmography/view/1/938/ Greek Film Archive (Film Museum) \u2013 NAKED IN THE STREET 1969]</ref></small>\n|\n[[Giannis Dalianidis]]\n|\n\"Asteri sto parathyro\", \"Dio aderfia\"\n|-\n|1969\n|\nO MPLOFATZIS <small>(\u03a4he bluffer)<ref>[http://www.tainiothiki.gr/v2/lang_en/filmography/view/1/339/ Greek Film Archive (Film Museum) \u2013 BLUFFER (THE) 1969]</ref></small>\n|\n[[Vasilis Georgiadis]]\n|\n\"Pios ein' aftos\"\n|-\n|1969\n|\nI PARIZIANA <small>(The Parisienne)<ref>[http://www.tainiothiki.gr/v2/lang_en/filmography/view/1/1781/ Greek Film Archive (Film Museum) \u2013 PARISIENNE (THE) 1969]</ref></small>\n|\n[[Giannis Dalianidis]]\n|\n\"Dos' mou t' athanato nero\", \"Zografismena sto harti\",\n\"To megalo finale tis Parizianas\"\n|-\n|1969\n|\nISAIA MI HOREVIS <small>(No wedding dance)<ref>[http://www.tainiothiki.gr/v2/lang_en/filmography/view/1/1030/ Greek Film Archive (Film Museum) \u2013 NO WEDDING DANCE 1969]</ref></small>\n|\n[[Kostas Karagiannis]]\n|\n\"Pali tha klapso\"\n|-\n|1970\n|\nKRIMA TO MPOI SOU <small>(What a waste)<ref>[http://www.tainiothiki.gr/v2/lang_en/filmography/view/1/1282/ Greek Film Archive (Film Museum) \u2013 WHAT A WASTE! 1970]</ref></small>\n|\n[[Kostas Karagiannis]]\n|\n\"Krima to mpoi sou\"\n|}\n\n==Video sampling==\n* {{YouTube|3dIjMyDN08g|Video of Marinella singing the song \"Kyra Giorgena\" at the TV show \"Nana Mouskouri with the Athenians\" on BBC, in 1971}}\n* {{YouTube|tlQqT7ywS1Q|Video clip of the song \"Krasi, thalassa ke t' agori mu\" (Eurovision '74) 1974}}\n* {{YouTube|MhHGKW3RA88|Video clip of the song \"Na pezi to tranzistor\" (\u0391lbum \"I Marinella tou simera\") 1978}}\n* {{YouTube|6oW0QafFd8o|Video clip of the song \"Vasanismeni Kyriaki\" (\u0391lbum \"Gia proti fora\") 1997}}\n* {{YouTube|mmp0oEqL6l8|Marinella singing the song \"Asteri sto parathyro (Star in the window)\" (Film \"Gymni sto dromo\") in 1969}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20120512003121/http://clubs.pathfinder.gr/marinella_diva/240572 Marinella \u2013 Fan Club in Pathfinder]\n*[http://www.marinella.dom.gr \u039c\u0391\u03a1\u0399\u039d\u0395\u039b\u039b\u0391 \u2013 \u0394\u03b9\u03b1\u03b4\u03b9\u03ba\u03c4\u03c5\u03b1\u03ba\u03cc \u0391\u03c6\u03b9\u03ad\u03c1\u03c9\u03bc\u03b1]\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{Succession box|\n  before=''none'' |\n  title=[[Greece in the Eurovision Song Contest]] |\n  years='''[[Eurovision Song Contest 1974|1974]]'''|\n  after=[[Mariza Koch]]<br>with ''[[Panayia Mou, Panayia Mou]]'' |\n}}\n{{S-end}}\n\n{{Music of Southeastern Europe (the Balkans)}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Marinella}}\n[[Category:1938 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Arion Music Awards winners]]\n[[Category:Eastern Orthodox Christians from Greece]]\n[[Category:Eurovision Song Contest entrants of 1974]]\n[[Category:Greek actresses]]\n[[Category:Greek Eurovision Song Contest entrants]]\n[[Category:Greek female singers]]\n[[Category:Greek la\u00efko singers]]\n[[Category:Greek entehno singers]]\n[[Category:Greek rebetiko singers]]\n[[Category:Universal Music Greece artists]]\n[[Category:PolyGram Records (Greece) artists]]\n[[Category:Minos EMI artists]]\n[[Category:Modern Greek-language singers]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Thessaloniki]]\n[[Category:Singers from Thessaloniki]]\n[[Category:Thessaloniki Song Festival entrants]]\n[[Category:Greek Macedonians]]\n", "name_user": "Graham87", "label": "safe", "comment": "typo", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Marinella"}
{"title_page": "Steller's sea ape", "text_new": "{{Infobox mythical creature|name=Steller's sea ape|Region=Aleutian Islands, Alaska|Country=United States|First_Reported=1741|Grouping=Mammalian|Habitat=Ocean}}\n\n{{good article}}\n{{short description|Purported marine mammal}}\n'''Steller's sea ape''' is a purported [[marine mammal]], observed by German zoologist [[Georg Steller]] on August 10, 1741, around the [[Shumagin Islands]] in Alaska. The animal was described as being around five feet, or one and a half meters long, with a dog-like head, long drooping whiskers; an elongated but robust body, thick fur coat, and no limbs but for two tail fins much like a shark. He described the creature as being playful and inquisitive, much like a monkey. After observing it for two hours, he attempted to shoot and collect the creature, but missed, and the creature swam away. A similar creature was seen in June, 1965, by sailor [[Miles Smeeton]] and company off [[Atka Island]], Alaska.\n\nThere have been four attempts to scientifically classify the creature, [[species description|described]] as ''Simia marina'', ''Siren cynocephala'', ''Trichechus hydropithecus'', and ''Manatus simia''. Steller most likely simply misidentified a [[Northern fur seal]].\n\n==Accounts==\n===Original account===\n====Observations====\n{{Location map+ | Alaska\n| relief  = 2\n| width   = 250\n| float   = right\n| caption = Locations of purported sightings\n| places =\n{{Location map~ | Alaska\n |Alaska\n |label=Shumagin Islands\n |link=Shumagin Islands\n |lat=55.228056\n |long=-160.018056\n |position=right\n}}\n{{Location map~ | Alaska\n |Alaska\n |label=Atka Island\n |link=Atka Island\n |lat=52.13806\n |long=-174.4453\n |position=right\n}}\n}}\nGerman zoologist [[Georg Steller]], aboard the ship ''St. Peter'' on [[Vitus Bering]]'s [[Great Northern Expedition]] (1733\u20131743), [[species description|described]] several new species during the voyage. At around sunset on August 10, 1741, near [[Shumagin Islands]], Alaska, Steller reported a strange and unidentifiable creature floating near the ship.<ref name=Stellar1742>{{cite book|first=G. W.|last=Steller|authorlink=Georg Wilhelm Steller|title=Journal of a Voyage with Bering, 1741\u20131742|editor1-first=O.|editor1-last=Frost|translator-first=M.|translator-last=Engel|publisher=Stanford University Press|pages=82\u201383|url={{google books|plainurl=yes|id=VtJY90BJ1yMC|page=79}}|isbn=978-0-8047-2181-3|year=1993}}</ref> \n\nThe creature purportedly stared at the ship for 2 hours\u2013according to Steller, seemingly out of admiration\u2013and got so close to the ship that it could have been poked by a pole. However, he said that whenever the crew attempted to approach the creature, it would swim farther out. He said it raised a third of its body out of the water, maintaining a human-like posture, for several minutes. After a half hour, the creature dove under the water and swam underneath the ship to the other side, and did this repeatedly about 30 times.<ref name=Stellar1742/>\n\nSteller stated that, when a large [[seaweed]] stalk about {{cvt|3\u20134|fathom|ft m}} long floated by, the creature quickly swam towards it and grabbed it with its mouth. The creature then swam closer to the ship and, purportedly, did juggling tricks with it like a trained monkey, though eating pieces of it now and again.<ref name=Stellar1742/> Steller's description of it as a sea-monkey probably stemmed more from such behavior rather than actual resemblance to a monkey.<ref name=Stejneger/>\n\nSteller attempted to collect the animal, so he took a gun and fired at it, but missed. He reported that the creature disappeared for a moment, but quickly came back, frightened, and once again gradually neared the ship. Steller fired at it again, but missed or only wounded the creature, which swam away. It was not seen again.<ref name=Stellar1742/>\n\n====Description====\nSteller reported the creature as being 2 [[ell]]s long, the combined length of the forearm and extended hand. It purportedly had a dog-like head, with pointed and erect ears, large eyes, and whiskers on the upper and lower lips resembling a [[Fu Manchu mustache]].<ref name=Stellar1742/>\n\nHe described the body as being long and fat, and thinning towards the tail. He said the creature had a thick fur coat, which was gray on the back and reddish-white on the belly. The author did not see any forelimbs or pectoral fins. The tail apparently had two fins, the upper fin double the size of the lower fin, much like a shark.<ref name=Stellar1742/>\n\n===Other accounts===\nIn June 1965, on his [[ketch]] (''Tzu Hang''), a sailor [[Miles Smeeton]], his daughter Clio and his friend Henry Combe purportedly saw a similar creature on the northern coast of [[Atka Island]]. They reported the creature as being about {{cvt|5|ft|m}} long, and having {{cvt|4\u20135|in|cm|adj=on}} reddish-yellow fur, and a face resembling that of the dog breed [[shih-tzu]]. He details this 10\u201315 second encounter in his book ''Misty Island'', noting Steller's observations closely matched his own.<ref>{{cite book|first=M.|last=Smeeton|authorlink=Miles and Beryl Smeeton|year=1969|title=The Misty Islands|publisher=Grafton|pages=109\u2013110|isbn=978-0-246-13489-9}}</ref>\n\n==Research history==\n[[File:Animal drawings collected by Felix Platter, p1 - (31).jpg|upright|thumb|''Simia marina'' in [[Conrad Gessner]]'s ''[[Historia animalium (Gessner)|Historia animalium]]'']]\nAll Steller's writings regarding his expedition were published posthumously, but most of his writings were lost. His account of the creature was detailed in his diary, published in 2 installments by Prussian zoologist [[Peter Simon Pallas]] in 1781 and 1793.<ref name=Stellar1742/> He also made a small note in his most famous book ''De Bestiis Marinus'', calling it an \"imperfect account\" for lack of a specimen:\n{{quote|text=I describe the traces of a certain unknown animal upon the island of Shumagin, and I insert a sketch of a sea ape, and with this imperfect account I must content myself and others.<ref>{{cite book|first=G. W.|last=Steller|authorlink=Georg Wilhelm Steller|origyear=1751|year=1899|chapter=On the Beasts of the Sea|title=The Fur Seals and Fur-Seal Islands of the North Pacific Ocean|editor-first=D. S.|editor-last=Jones|translator1-first=W.|translator1-last=Miller|translator2-first=J. E.|translator2-last=Miller|publisher=Stanford University Press|url=https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/111304#page/243|page=181}}</ref>}}\n\nSteller assigned this creature to \"''Simia marina''\"\u2013which was illustrated in Swiss naturalist [[Conrad Gessner]]'s book ''[[Historia animalium (Gessner)|Historia animalium]]''\u2013based on its resemblance, strange behavior, rapid movements, and playfulness.<ref name=Stellar1742/> However, the man who first reported \"''S. marina''\", Italian biologist [[Gerolamo Cardano]], said it was likely a snake, and Gessner said that it had a covering more like a turtle, and the creature was reportedly green and hairless overall.<ref>{{cite book|url=https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/42166528#page/943|first=C.|last=Gessner|authorlink=Conrad Gessner|title=Historia animalium|language=Latin|trans-title=History of the animals|pages=877\u2013878|publisher=In Bibliopolio Andreae Cambieri|year=1604}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|first=S.|last=Hendrikx|year=2018|title=Monstrosities from the Sea. Taxonomy and tradition in Conrad Gessner's (1516\u20131565) discussion of cetaceans and sea-monsters|journal=Anthropozoologica|volume=53|issue=11|url=https://www.researchgate.net/publication/326803926|page=136<!--only citing this page-->|doi=10.5252/anthropozoologica2018v53a11|hdl=1887/67726}}</ref> At least 5 years had passed since Steller last saw or read a description of Gessner's sea ape to when he had described his account.<ref name=Stellar1742/> \n\n[[File:FMIB 45370 Fur-Seals rising to breathe and look around.jpeg|thumb|left|Steller may have misidentified a [[Northern fur seal]] (above)]]\nIn 1792, German naturalist [[Johann Julius Walbaum]] scientifically described Steller's sea ape as ''Siren cynocephala''.<ref>{{cite book|url=https://archive.org/details/petriartedisueci03arte|first=J. J.|last=Walbaum|authorlink=Johann Julius Walbaum|year=1792|title=Petri Artedi Sueci Genera piscium|language=Latin|trans-title=Swede Peter Artedi's fish genera|series=Ichthyologiae|publisher=Grypeswaldi\u00e6|page=[https://archive.org/details/petriartedisueci03arte/page/560 560]}}</ref> In 1800, on recommendation by Welsh naturalist [[Thomas Pennant]], English zoologist [[George Shaw]] classified it as a [[manatee]] as ''Trichechus hydropithecus''.<ref>{{cite book|url=https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/128108#page/412|first=G.|last=Shaw|year=1800|title=General zoology, or Systematic natural history|volume=1|publisher=Thomas Davison, White-Friars|pages=247\u2013248}}</ref> In 1815, German zoologist [[Johann Karl Wilhelm Illiger]] also described it as a manatee as ''Manatus simia'',<ref>{{cite journal|first=J. K. W.|last=Illiger|authorlink=Johann Karl Wilhelm Illiger|year=1815|title=Ueberblick der S\u00e4ugthiere nach ihrer Vertheilung \u00fcber die Weltlheile|language=German|trans-title=Overview of Mammals and their Distribution over the World|journal=Abhandlungen der K\u00f6niglich Preussischen Akademie der Wissenschaften|page=53}}</ref> but this work in particular was later called a \"worthless conglomeration\" of [[sirenia]]n and [[cetacea]]n species by American mammalogist [[Joel Asaph Allen]] in 1882, with new species listed for seemingly no reason without description or justification.<ref>{{cite book|first=J. A.|last=Allen|authorlink=Joel Asaph Allen|year=1882|title=Preliminary List of Works and Papers Relating to the Mammalian Orders Cete and Sirenia|publisher=Bulletin of the United States Geological and Geographical Survey of the Territories|url={{google books|plainurl=yes|id=gmnck8OU-DQC|page=499}}|page=499}}</ref>\n\nIn 1805, German naturalist [[Wilhelm Gottlieb Tilesius von Tilenau]] noticed that Steller's sea ape very closely resembled the [[Northern fur seal]].<ref>{{cite journal|first=W. G.|last=Tilesius|authorlink=Wilhelm Gottlieb Tilesius von Tilenau|year=1835|title=Die Wallfische|language=German|trans-title=The Whales|publisher=Isis von Oken|volume=28|page=715}}</ref> Similarly, in 1936, Norwegian zoologist [[Leonhard Stejneger]] said Steller likely observed a bachelor [[fur seal]], as fur seals in a playful mood have been known to exhibit the observed behaviors, and swim with their fore-flipper tucked in, which may have given the impression of completely lacking forelimbs in a low light setting. Also, Steller had made his account before he had ever encountered a fur seal.<ref name=Stejneger>{{cite book|first=L. H.|last=Stejneger|authorlink=Leonhard Stejneger|year=1936|title=Georg Wilhelm Steller, the pioneer of Alaskan natural history|url=https://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=uc1.31822011666914&view=1up&seq=332|publisher=Harvard University Press|pages=278\u2013281}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Waitoreke]]\n* [[Steller's sea cow]]\n* [[Steller sea lion]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:1741 in science]]\n[[Category:Purported mammals]]\n[[Category:Cryptozoology articles needing infoboxes]]\n[[Category:Mammal cryptids]]\n[[Category:Aquatic cryptids]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox mythical creature|name=Steller's Sea Ape|Region=Aleutian Islands, Alaska|Country=United States|First_Reported=1741|Grouping=Mammalian|Habitat=Ocean}}\n\n{{good article}}\n{{short description|Purported marine mammal}}\n'''Steller's sea ape''' is a purported [[marine mammal]], observed by German zoologist [[Georg Steller]] on August 10, 1741, around the [[Shumagin Islands]] in Alaska. The animal was described as being around five feet, or one and a half meters long, with a dog-like head, long drooping whiskers; an elongated but robust body, thick fur coat, and no limbs but for two tail fins much like a shark. He described the creature as being playful and inquisitive, much like a monkey. After observing it for two hours, he attempted to shoot and collect the creature, but missed, and the creature swam away. A similar creature was seen in June, 1965, by sailor [[Miles Smeeton]] and company off [[Atka Island]], Alaska.\n\nThere have been four attempts to scientifically classify the creature, [[species description|described]] as ''Simia marina'', ''Siren cynocephala'', ''Trichechus hydropithecus'', and ''Manatus simia''. Steller most likely simply misidentified a [[Northern fur seal]].\n\n==Accounts==\n===Original account===\n====Observations====\n{{Location map+ | Alaska\n| relief  = 2\n| width   = 250\n| float   = right\n| caption = Locations of purported sightings\n| places =\n{{Location map~ | Alaska\n |Alaska\n |label=Shumagin Islands\n |link=Shumagin Islands\n |lat=55.228056\n |long=-160.018056\n |position=right\n}}\n{{Location map~ | Alaska\n |Alaska\n |label=Atka Island\n |link=Atka Island\n |lat=52.13806\n |long=-174.4453\n |position=right\n}}\n}}\nGerman zoologist [[Georg Steller]], aboard the ship ''St. Peter'' on [[Vitus Bering]]'s [[Great Northern Expedition]] (1733\u20131743), [[species description|described]] several new species during the voyage. At around sunset on August 10, 1741, near [[Shumagin Islands]], Alaska, Steller reported a strange and unidentifiable creature floating near the ship.<ref name=Stellar1742>{{cite book|first=G. W.|last=Steller|authorlink=Georg Wilhelm Steller|title=Journal of a Voyage with Bering, 1741\u20131742|editor1-first=O.|editor1-last=Frost|translator-first=M.|translator-last=Engel|publisher=Stanford University Press|pages=82\u201383|url={{google books|plainurl=yes|id=VtJY90BJ1yMC|page=79}}|isbn=978-0-8047-2181-3|year=1993}}</ref> \n\nThe creature purportedly stared at the ship for 2 hours\u2013according to Steller, seemingly out of admiration\u2013and got so close to the ship that it could have been poked by a pole. However, he said that whenever the crew attempted to approach the creature, it would swim farther out. He said it raised a third of its body out of the water, maintaining a human-like posture, for several minutes. After a half hour, the creature dove under the water and swam underneath the ship to the other side, and did this repeatedly about 30 times.<ref name=Stellar1742/>\n\nSteller stated that, when a large [[seaweed]] stalk about {{cvt|3\u20134|fathom|ft m}} long floated by, the creature quickly swam towards it and grabbed it with its mouth. The creature then swam closer to the ship and, purportedly, did juggling tricks with it like a trained monkey, though eating pieces of it now and again.<ref name=Stellar1742/> Steller's description of it as a sea-monkey probably stemmed more from such behavior rather than actual resemblance to a monkey.<ref name=Stejneger/>\n\nSteller attempted to collect the animal, so he took a gun and fired at it, but missed. He reported that the creature disappeared for a moment, but quickly came back, frightened, and once again gradually neared the ship. Steller fired at it again, but missed or only wounded the creature, which swam away. It was not seen again.<ref name=Stellar1742/>\n\n====Description====\nSteller reported the creature as being 2 [[ell]]s long, the combined length of the forearm and extended hand. It purportedly had a dog-like head, with pointed and erect ears, large eyes, and whiskers on the upper and lower lips resembling a [[Fu Manchu mustache]].<ref name=Stellar1742/>\n\nHe described the body as being long and fat, and thinning towards the tail. He said the creature had a thick fur coat, which was gray on the back and reddish-white on the belly. The author did not see any forelimbs or pectoral fins. The tail apparently had two fins, the upper fin double the size of the lower fin, much like a shark.<ref name=Stellar1742/>\n\n===Other accounts===\nIn June 1965, on his [[ketch]] (''Tzu Hang''), a sailor [[Miles Smeeton]], his daughter Clio and his friend Henry Combe purportedly saw a similar creature on the northern coast of [[Atka Island]]. They reported the creature as being about {{cvt|5|ft|m}} long, and having {{cvt|4\u20135|in|cm|adj=on}} reddish-yellow fur, and a face resembling that of the dog breed [[shih-tzu]]. He details this 10\u201315 second encounter in his book ''Misty Island'', noting Steller's observations closely matched his own.<ref>{{cite book|first=M.|last=Smeeton|authorlink=Miles and Beryl Smeeton|year=1969|title=The Misty Islands|publisher=Grafton|pages=109\u2013110|isbn=978-0-246-13489-9}}</ref>\n\n==Research history==\n[[File:Animal drawings collected by Felix Platter, p1 - (31).jpg|upright|thumb|''Simia marina'' in [[Conrad Gessner]]'s ''[[Historia animalium (Gessner)|Historia animalium]]'']]\nAll Steller's writings regarding his expedition were published posthumously, but most of his writings were lost. His account of the creature was detailed in his diary, published in 2 installments by Prussian zoologist [[Peter Simon Pallas]] in 1781 and 1793.<ref name=Stellar1742/> He also made a small note in his most famous book ''De Bestiis Marinus'', calling it an \"imperfect account\" for lack of a specimen:\n{{quote|text=I describe the traces of a certain unknown animal upon the island of Shumagin, and I insert a sketch of a sea ape, and with this imperfect account I must content myself and others.<ref>{{cite book|first=G. W.|last=Steller|authorlink=Georg Wilhelm Steller|origyear=1751|year=1899|chapter=On the Beasts of the Sea|title=The Fur Seals and Fur-Seal Islands of the North Pacific Ocean|editor-first=D. S.|editor-last=Jones|translator1-first=W.|translator1-last=Miller|translator2-first=J. E.|translator2-last=Miller|publisher=Stanford University Press|url=https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/111304#page/243|page=181}}</ref>}}\n\nSteller assigned this creature to \"''Simia marina''\"\u2013which was illustrated in Swiss naturalist [[Conrad Gessner]]'s book ''[[Historia animalium (Gessner)|Historia animalium]]''\u2013based on its resemblance, strange behavior, rapid movements, and playfulness.<ref name=Stellar1742/> However, the man who first reported \"''S. marina''\", Italian biologist [[Gerolamo Cardano]], said it was likely a snake, and Gessner said that it had a covering more like a turtle, and the creature was reportedly green and hairless overall.<ref>{{cite book|url=https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/42166528#page/943|first=C.|last=Gessner|authorlink=Conrad Gessner|title=Historia animalium|language=Latin|trans-title=History of the animals|pages=877\u2013878|publisher=In Bibliopolio Andreae Cambieri|year=1604}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|first=S.|last=Hendrikx|year=2018|title=Monstrosities from the Sea. Taxonomy and tradition in Conrad Gessner's (1516\u20131565) discussion of cetaceans and sea-monsters|journal=Anthropozoologica|volume=53|issue=11|url=https://www.researchgate.net/publication/326803926|page=136<!--only citing this page-->|doi=10.5252/anthropozoologica2018v53a11|hdl=1887/67726}}</ref> At least 5 years had passed since Steller last saw or read a description of Gessner's sea ape to when he had described his account.<ref name=Stellar1742/> \n\n[[File:FMIB 45370 Fur-Seals rising to breathe and look around.jpeg|thumb|left|Steller may have misidentified a [[Northern fur seal]] (above)]]\nIn 1792, German naturalist [[Johann Julius Walbaum]] scientifically described Steller's sea ape as ''Siren cynocephala''.<ref>{{cite book|url=https://archive.org/details/petriartedisueci03arte|first=J. J.|last=Walbaum|authorlink=Johann Julius Walbaum|year=1792|title=Petri Artedi Sueci Genera piscium|language=Latin|trans-title=Swede Peter Artedi's fish genera|series=Ichthyologiae|publisher=Grypeswaldi\u00e6|page=[https://archive.org/details/petriartedisueci03arte/page/560 560]}}</ref> In 1800, on recommendation by Welsh naturalist [[Thomas Pennant]], English zoologist [[George Shaw]] classified it as a [[manatee]] as ''Trichechus hydropithecus''.<ref>{{cite book|url=https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/128108#page/412|first=G.|last=Shaw|year=1800|title=General zoology, or Systematic natural history|volume=1|publisher=Thomas Davison, White-Friars|pages=247\u2013248}}</ref> In 1815, German zoologist [[Johann Karl Wilhelm Illiger]] also described it as a manatee as ''Manatus simia'',<ref>{{cite journal|first=J. K. W.|last=Illiger|authorlink=Johann Karl Wilhelm Illiger|year=1815|title=Ueberblick der S\u00e4ugthiere nach ihrer Vertheilung \u00fcber die Weltlheile|language=German|trans-title=Overview of Mammals and their Distribution over the World|journal=Abhandlungen der K\u00f6niglich Preussischen Akademie der Wissenschaften|page=53}}</ref> but this work in particular was later called a \"worthless conglomeration\" of [[sirenia]]n and [[cetacea]]n species by American mammalogist [[Joel Asaph Allen]] in 1882, with new species listed for seemingly no reason without description or justification.<ref>{{cite book|first=J. A.|last=Allen|authorlink=Joel Asaph Allen|year=1882|title=Preliminary List of Works and Papers Relating to the Mammalian Orders Cete and Sirenia|publisher=Bulletin of the United States Geological and Geographical Survey of the Territories|url={{google books|plainurl=yes|id=gmnck8OU-DQC|page=499}}|page=499}}</ref>\n\nIn 1805, German naturalist [[Wilhelm Gottlieb Tilesius von Tilenau]] noticed that Steller's sea ape very closely resembled the [[Northern fur seal]].<ref>{{cite journal|first=W. G.|last=Tilesius|authorlink=Wilhelm Gottlieb Tilesius von Tilenau|year=1835|title=Die Wallfische|language=German|trans-title=The Whales|publisher=Isis von Oken|volume=28|page=715}}</ref> Similarly, in 1936, Norwegian zoologist [[Leonhard Stejneger]] said Steller likely observed a bachelor [[fur seal]], as fur seals in a playful mood have been known to exhibit the observed behaviors, and swim with their fore-flipper tucked in, which may have given the impression of completely lacking forelimbs in a low light setting. Also, Steller had made his account before he had ever encountered a fur seal.<ref name=Stejneger>{{cite book|first=L. H.|last=Stejneger|authorlink=Leonhard Stejneger|year=1936|title=Georg Wilhelm Steller, the pioneer of Alaskan natural history|url=https://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=uc1.31822011666914&view=1up&seq=332|publisher=Harvard University Press|pages=278\u2013281}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Waitoreke]]\n* [[Steller's sea cow]]\n* [[Steller sea lion]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:1741 in science]]\n[[Category:Purported mammals]]\n[[Category:Cryptozoology articles needing infoboxes]]\n[[Category:Mammal cryptids]]\n[[Category:Aquatic cryptids]]\n", "name_user": "WolfmanSF", "label": "safe", "comment": "-> lower case", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Steller%27s_sea_ape"}
{"title_page": "Anti-Russian violence in Chechnya (1991\u20131994)", "text_new": "{{short description|Violent actions and segregation between 1990 and 2005}}\n{{Campaignbox First Chechen War|state=expanded}}\n{{multiple issues|{{Original research|date=December 2019}}{{Accuracy dispute|date=December 2019}}}}\n'''[[Anti-Russian sentiment|Anti-Russian violence]] was recorded in [[Chechnya]]''' ({{lang-ru|\u042d\u0442\u043d\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0435 \u0447\u0438\u0441\u0442\u043a\u0438 \u0432 \u0427\u0435\u0447\u043d\u0435}}). The violent acts were committed against [[Russians|Russian]] and non-Chechen civilians in Chechnya from 1991 to 1994. Tens of thousands of Russians left Chechnya.\n\n== Background ==\nDuring the 1990s, Chechen leaders accused the Russian government of attempting genocide against the ethnic Chechen population.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.inosmi.ru/text/translation/140373.html|title=The deepest Western silence as the reply to Chechen nation's genocide|date=2002-03-25|work=[[Le Figaro]]|publisher=inosmi.ru|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090318010733/http://www.inosmi.ru/text/translation/140373.html|archivedate=2009-03-18}} [http://www.chechenpress.info/news/2004/01/02/03.shtml] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191206130631/http://www.chechenpress.info/news/2004/01/02/03.shtml|date=2019-12-06}}</ref> Some politicians{{Clarify|reason=|date=December 2019}} used these terms to describe the actions of both sides.{{Citation needed|date=December 2019}} In a 2006 interview, Yuri Ivanov, a former member of the Russian government, claimed to have seen camps in Chechnya between 1993 and 1995 where hundreds of thousands of Russians, Greeks, and religious minorities were interned in Chechnya in what he described as a genocide.<ref>[http://www.echo.msk.ru/programs/exit/42883/ Echo of Moscow, radio show Ischem Vykhod (Looking for Exit), theme \"Is there the independent justice in Russia] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191206130639/https://echo.msk.ru/programs/exit/42883/|date=2019-12-06}}, 12 April 2006</ref>\n\nIn 2010 [[Alexander Khloponin]] said that the migration of the Russian-speaking population from Chechnya to other regions of Russia in the 1990s was due primarily to economic pressures.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rg.ru/2010/05/27/hloponin.html|title=\u0427\u0430\u0441 \u0432\u043e\u0439\u043d\u0435, \u043d\u043e \u0432\u0440\u0435\u043c\u044f \u2014 \u0436\u0438\u0437\u043d\u0438|trans-title=An hour for war, the time for life|publisher=[[Rossiyskaya gazeta]]|date=2010-05-27|access-date=2019-12-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191206131655/https://rg.ru/2010/05/27/hloponin.html|archive-date=2019-12-06|url-status=live}} No. 5192 (113)'</ref> According to a report published by the [[Moscow Helsinki Group]] in 2006, while many former Soviet republics saw the mass emigration of Russian speakers to Russia, only in Chechnya was this emigration primarily spurred by anti-Russian sentiment and the threat of violence.<ref name=\":2\">[http://www.mhg.ru/files/knigi/prksen1.pdf Opposing xenophobia and ethnic discrimination courses] (https://web.archive.org/web/20090611185909/http://www.mhg.ru/files/knigi/prksen1.pdf Archive])</ref> Local Chechen attitudes increasingly blamed Russia for their economic and political troubles, and viewed ethnic Russians as hostile \"colonizers\" of Chechnya.<ref name=\":2\" />\n\nRussian commentators have described the animosity between Chechens and Russians as a conflict that has persisted since Russia's attempts to consolidate the territory into its empire in the 18th century.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ng.ru/regions/2002-05-23/5_leeder.html|title=\u0421\u0435\u0433\u043e\u0434\u043d\u044f\u0448\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u0441\u043e\u0431\u044b\u0442\u0438\u044f \u2014 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0434\u043e\u043b\u0436\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u041a\u0430\u0432\u043a\u0430\u0437\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u0432\u043e\u0439\u043d\u044b|trans-title=Today events are the continuation of the Caucasus War|publisher=Nezavisimaya gazeta|date=2002-05-23|access-date=2019-12-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191206130629/http://www.ng.ru/regions/2002-05-23/5_leeder.html|archive-date=2019-12-06|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nA [[Central Intelligence Agency|CIA]] report in 1992 documents that as of its publication, roughly 50,000 ethnic Russians had left Chechnya due to fears of violence<ref>[https://www.cia.gov/library/readingroom/docs/DOC_0000837999.pdf The punished peoples: a primer on Russia's North Caucasus] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170913183802/https://www.cia.gov/library/readingroom/docs/DOC_0000837999.pdf |date=2017-09-13 }} CIA's Directorate of Intelligence file, 2 April 1992</ref>\n\nAccording to [[Soviet Census (1989)|All-Union Census of 1989]], there were 1,270,429 residents of  [[Checheno-Ingush Autonomous Soviet Socialist Republic|Checheno-Ingush ASSR]], including 734,501 Chechens, 293,771 Russians, 163,762 Ingushes, 14,824 Armenians, 14,824 Tatars, 12,637 Nogai people etc.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://demoscope.ru/weekly/ssp/rus_nac_89.php?reg=49|title=Soviet Census 1989|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190403210621/http://www.demoscope.ru/weekly/ssp/rus_nac_89.php?reg=49|archive-date=2019-04-03|access-date=2019-12-06}}</ref> The population of Chechnya was 1,100,000 residents,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ethno-kavkaz.narod.ru/rnchechenia.html|title=Ethno-Caucasus. Population of Chechnya districts in 1989|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191013234204/http://www.ethno-kavkaz.narod.ru/rnchechenia.html|archive-date=2019-10-13|access-date=2019-12-06}}</ref> including 397,000 people of [[Grozny]] (210,000 Russians).<ref name=\"Appeal\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.obraschenie.front.ru/|title=\u041e\u0431\u0440\u0430\u0449\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u043e\u0431 \u043e\u0444\u0438\u0446\u0438\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u043e\u043c \u043f\u0440\u0438\u0437\u043d\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0438 \u0413\u0435\u043d\u043e\u0446\u0438\u0434\u0430 \u0440\u0443\u0441\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0445 \u0432 \u0427\u0435\u0447\u043d\u0435|trans-title=Appeal on official recognition of Russian people genocide in Chechnya|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070415231013/http://www.obraschenie.front.ru/|archivedate=2007-04-15|accessdate=2007-05-05}}</ref>\n\n== Oppression of Russian people during Dudayev regime ==\nAccording to [[Izvestiya]] newspaper, the persecutions of Russian began in 1990s, starting with threatening letters telling Russians to leave in 1990, followed by the disappearances of Russian girls and reports of Russian men being assaulted.<ref name=\":12\">[https://archive.today/20120530021036/www.izvestia.ru/russia/article1092129/ Forgotten Genocide]. [[Izvestiya]], 28 January 2005</ref> Russian government officials have described the ensuing events as a genocide, and described various anti-Russian slogans attributed to Chechens which called for the expulsion and/or enslavement of Russians.<ref name=\":02\">[http://www.specnaz.ru/article/?1267 Gates of Thunder] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170913231033/http://www.specnaz.ru/article/?1267|date=2017-09-13}} Spetsnaz Rossii, issue 5 (14), May 2008 {{in lang|ru}}</ref><ref>[http://svpressa.ru/society/article/66089/ Return to Ingushetia] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191206130707/https://svpressa.ru/society/article/66089/|date=2019-12-06}} ID Svobodnaya Pressa, 12 June 2013,</ref>\n\n[[BBC Russian Service]] describes local Communist Party official Vitaly Kutsenko as having been the first casualty of anti-Russian violence leading up to the [[First Chechen War]] when he was assaulted by supporters of [[Dzhokhar Dudayev]] and members of National Congress of Chechen People. Conflicting reports allege that either Kutsenko was thrown out of a window of his office, or died from falling after trying to escape out a window.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/russian/russia/2009/12/091210_chechnya_war_history|title=\u041f\u0435\u0440\u0432\u0430\u044f \u0447\u0435\u0447\u0435\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0430\u044f: \u043f\u0443\u0442\u044c \u043a \u0432\u043e\u0439\u043d\u0435|author=\u0410\u0440\u0442\u0435\u043c \u041a\u0440\u0435\u0447\u0435\u0442\u043d\u0438\u043a\u043e\u0432|date=2009-12-10|website=BBC News Russian Service|language=ru|accessdate=2019-12-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171025105730/http://www.bbc.com/russian/russia/2009/12/091210_chechnya_war_history|archive-date=2017-10-25|url-status=live}}</ref>  According to Russian political commentators, the lack of action from the Soviet government in response to this assault further emboldened Chechen forces to carry out violence against Russians.<ref>[http://www.kommersant.ru/doc.aspx?fromsearch=ac89d082-b347-4736-85b9-eb7ff6a28869&docsid=281761 Day of Banditism, Terrorism and Arbitrariness] Kommersant, No. 161 (2291), 6 September 2001]</ref><ref>[http://www.rg.ru/2009/10/08/edelev.html Checkists capture Staff] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191206131217/https://rg.ru/2009/10/08/edelev.html |date=2019-12-06 }} [[Rossiyskaya Gazeta]], No. 5013 (189)</ref>\n\nThe residents of Assinovskaya, Sunzhensky Disctict, Chechnya have sent open letter to President of Russia [[Boris Yeltsin]], in which they named all the cases of assaults on Russian people and murders of them. According to the letter, 26 Russian families had been murdered since August 1996 and more than 52 households were kidnapped by the Chechen forces.<ref name=\"trudgenoc\">[http://conrad2001.narod.ru/russian/genocide/genocide_8.htm Vladimir Yanchenkov. Documentary evidence of genocide of Russians in Mashakdov's Ichkeriya] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150725204149/http://conrad2001.narod.ru/russian/genocide/genocide_8.htm|date=2015-07-25}}, Trud, 17 February 2000</ref> Another appeal made by 50 thousand residents of Naursky and Shelkovsky Districts was mentioned in a book published by Rosinformcenter.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.fsb.ru/history/book/white/white.html |title=Archived copy |access-date=2019-12-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080419125844/http://www.fsb.ru/history/book/white/white.html |archive-date=2008-04-19 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref name=\"white book\">{{Cite web |url=http://conrad2001.narod.ru/russian/library/books/wh_book_3/wh_book_3-6.htm |title=\"Chechnya. White Book.\" Moscow, 2000. RIA Novosti, Rosinformcenter |access-date=2019-12-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150724030428/http://conrad2001.narod.ru/russian/library/books/wh_book_3/wh_book_3-6.htm |archive-date=2015-07-24 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nPeople fleeing Chechnya could not get refugee status because, according to Russian laws, the refugee status could be offered only during migration to another country, therefore those people were considered as \"internally displaced persons\".<ref>[http://www.trud.ru/issue/article.php?id=200002170300502 Outcasts in Homeland] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191206130658/http://www.trud.ru/issue/article.php%3Fid%3D200002170300502|date=2019-12-06}} Trud // No.30, 17 February 2000]</ref> According to ethnologist Valery Tishkov, almost all non-Chechen (mostly Russian) population was expelled or exterminated during war by locals; about 200 thousand people have to run away from Grozny, however, Russian authorities and world community were completely indifferent to their problems.<ref>[http://www.valerytishkov.ru/cntnt/publikacii3/lekcii2/video/chechenska1.html Chechen War. Anthropologist' view, part 1 by Valery Tishkov] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190522033149/http://www.valerytishkov.ru/cntnt/publikacii3/lekcii2/video/chechenska1.html|date=2019-05-22}} (see 85:00)</ref> During 1990s a large inscription reading \"Russians, do not leave us, we need slaves and prostitutes\" appeared at the entry of the city of Grozny.<ref>{{cite web|last=\u0421\u043e\u0448\u0438\u043d|first=\u042e\u0440\u0438\u0439|publisher=\u0418\u043d\u0444\u043e\u0440\u043c\u0430\u0446\u0438\u043e\u043d\u043d\u043e-\u0430\u043d\u0430\u043b\u0438\u0442\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u044d\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0442\u0440\u043e\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u0436\u0443\u0440\u043d\u0430\u043b \u00ab\u0424\u0430\u043a\u0442\u00bb #23|url=http://www.fact.ru/www/arhiv23bez-2.htm|title=\u0411\u043e\u043b\u044c\u0448\u043e\u0439 \u043a\u0430\u0432\u043a\u0430\u0437\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0442\u0443\u043f\u0438\u043a|language=ru|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110706102600/http://www.fact.ru/www/arhiv23bez-2.htm|archivedate=2011-07-06}}</ref>\n\nOn 17 June 1993 Council of Nations of [[Supreme Soviet of Russia]] adopted statement \"Due to the situation in Chechen Republic\", in which it was stated that the policy of the Chechen authorities led to \"serious deterioration of different nations\", some of which \"are expelled over the borders of republic and have to leave places, where they and their ancestors had been living together with Chechens and Ingushes for many generations\".<ref>Statement of Council of Nations of Supreme Soviet of Russia, 17 June 1993, No. 5205-I \"\"Due to the situation in Chechen Republic\"</ref> But in October 1994 President of Chechen Republic of Ichkeriya Dzhokhar Dudayev claimed during an interview with [[Interfax]]  that reports of persecution of non-Chechen people in Ichkeriya was simply Russian propaganda, and highlighted proclamations made by his government against the persecution of Russians.<ref name=\"white book\" />\n\nIn 2006, [[Ziyad Sabsabi]] the Chechen Republic Prime Minister Deputy denied the occurrence of a genocide against Russians in Ichkeriya in 1992 and 1993, stating that\n{{quotation|We will not and are not going to silence [that]. However, I want to note that there was no genocide of particular nation: Jews, Armenians, Russians, Ukrainians etc. lived in Chechnya. But I can assure you, the victims of illegitimate armed groups were also Chechens, which suffered from them not less than Russians.<ref>[http://www.echo.msk.ru/programs/razvorot/48128/ Anniversary of Russian troops entering Chechnya. Current situation] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191206130639/https://echo.msk.ru/programs/razvorot/48128/ |date=2019-12-06 }}. Razvorot radio show, 11 December 2016, [[Echo of Moscow]]</ref>}}\n\n=== Examples ===\nOn 18 February 1992 an appeal of a woman who used to live in Grozny sooner was published. She informed on different criminal actions against Russian residents of the city:<ref name=\"white book\" /> \n{{quotation|[Chechens] threw us out during the middle of school year and did not leave us neither vacation, nor tickets or compensation. Then they started bullying children: for example, in a school with majority of Russian children bottles with mercury have been thrown, and girls were afraid to walk in the streets because indigenous youngsters pursued them and tried to kidnap them.\n\nThe situation is unbearable in transport and shops. One can't even buy bread without listening insults or provocations. Dudayev's gang of youngsters tried to enter our apartment at night (before elections), they were sliding daggers and screaming.}}\n\nAfter the military coup d'\u00e9tat by Dudayev total change of locals' attitude to military had changed: armed people have captured and destroyed internal troops regiment, aviation training regiment, anti-aircraft signals regiment. The assaults were performed by personnel of \"Cheborz\" company led by [[Shamil Basayev]]. Part of weapons and vehicles, all signal devices, car parts and other necessaries  have been stolen, and at the same time mass exodus of Russian-speaking population began.<ref name=\"white book\"/> [[Boris Yeltsin]] paid a lot of attention to that situation and mentioned in his statement from 19 October 1991:\n{{quotation|... during last weeks peaceful land of Checheno-Ingushetia turned into arena of mass riots and armed conflicts followed by capturing of government agencies, pogroms, misconducts and death of people... All actions taken during political negotiations, however, did not led to restitution of neither public law and order nor civilian concordance. Furthermore, situation becomes more and more unpredictable and may lead to the most critical impact for the present and the future of the Republic.}}\n\nAccording to ethnologist S.V.Chesko, nationalism is always connected to competition in areas for employment, material goods distribution, political rights and statuses and resources using, therefore during chaos in Chechnya many gangs and mobsters have captured commercial structures and industrial enterprises. Federal Government of Germany have provided aid for Chechnya expressed in education pioneer detachments of national armed forces.<ref>Cheshko S.V. Role of ethnic nationalism during USSR collapse // Tragedy of the Great Power: national question and Soviet Union Collapse / ed. by G. N. Sevostyanov. Completed by S.M.Ishakov. - Moscow: Social and Political Thought, 2005. {{ISBN|5-902168-41-4}}, 2005. p. 448.</ref>  In 2000 [[Rossiyskaya Gazeta]] published the general picture of events in Chechnya, paying attention to the facts of Russian-speaking people genocide:\n\n{{quotation|Almost total unemployment was in cities: men were walking with assault rifles, the law has disappeared, local armed squads ran rampant, their feuds were brutal. Fear, robberies, murders, kidnapping and slavery in streets of Grozny, beheading, drinking blood from glasses and public executions have conquered the city. Since 1990 the whole villages have been robbing the incoming trains, nowadays the railway connection has stopped. Bandit raids to Stavropol happened more often, the residents of suburbs were taken to slavery or as hostage, buses with passengers and helicopters were captured. The result was military intrusion of Chechens to Dagestan and terrorism acts in Russian cities. About 30 thousand of Russians in Chechnya were slaughtered, more than 200 thousand had to leave without apartments and property.<ref>[http://www.rg.ru/anons/arc_2000/0113/33.htm Rebuilding Chechnya, or why Ichkeriyan state failed] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191206130641/https://rg.ru/anons/arc_2000/0113/33.htm |date=2019-12-06 }} [[Rossiyskaya Gazeta]], 2000</ref>}}\n\n[[Security Council of Russia]] Secretary [[Ivan Rybkin]] (in 1996-1998) told about pre-war Grozny:\n{{quotation|There was anarchy in Chechnya. Russian city Grozny had really bad times. There was exodus of Russians, Tatars, Armenians and Jews caused by the pressure during this anarchy. They lost everything: apartments, cash, property, cars. It is necessary to say about hundreds of thousands people who left this biggest city of Northern Caucasus. I, as the State Duma Chariman, have got a letter directed to Boris Yeltsin and subscribed by 40 thousand people, where they expressed everything that happened in Chechnya. It was hard to read. My assistants come from those lands, from Terek \u2013 Nikolay Savchenko and Leonid Mayorov, stanitsas Kurskaya and Georgiyevskaya. They have brought this letter with tears in their eyes. [[Rossiyskaya Gazeta]] had published parts of this letter then.<ref>[http://echo.msk.ru/programs/razvorot/640337-echo/ 15th anniversary of Russian troops entering Chechnya] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191206130648/https://echo.msk.ru/programs/razvorot/640337-echo/ |date=2019-12-06 }}. [[Echo of Moscow]], Razvorot talk show, 11 December 2009</ref>}}\n\nAccording to human rights activists [[Memorial (society)|Memorial]], most of messages about human right abuses in Chechnya provided by Russian media were fake because Prosecutor and Ministry of Internal Affairs (MVD) have confirmed small part of those messages.<ref>Russia\u2014 Chechnya: chain of mistakes and crimes; O.P.Orlov, A.V.Cherkasov for Memorial</ref> [[Federal Counterintelligence Service]] did not accept any of applications with information on kidnappings or forced labor in Chechnya and did not conduct any operations or investigation, motivating that such questions are out of Service competence. Russian MVD and Prosecutor General officials stated that Russian and Chechen Internal Affairs Sections did not sign any agreements on functions distinction between two sides, so all crimes committed on Chechen territory had to be investigated by Chechnya law agencies.<ref>[http://www.kommersant.ru/doc/73427 Chechnya denies fact of Russian slaves existing] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191206132043/https://www.kommersant.ru/doc/73427 |date=2019-12-06 }} Kommersant, No. 44 (512), 12 March 1994</ref> However, there is an opinion, according to which all robberies and murders happened in a territory not controlled by any of the sides. The judge of Ramzes Goychaev case stated that the main reason for crime committing was not xenophobia but defenseless of Russians:<ref>[http://www.1tv.ru/news/crime/106941 First sentence in Pyatigorsk on the first criminal case on Russians genocide] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150215210915/http://www.1tv.ru/news/crime/106941 |date=2015-02-15 }} [[Channel One (Russia)|Channel One]], 18 April 2001</ref> former Mayor of [[Kovrov]] Irina Tabatskova told that during Chechen Wars Russians were shot and thrown out of windows by Chechens, who wanted to capture their apartments.<ref>[http://www.rus-obr.ru/ru-web/5974 Irina Tabatskova: Russians are not considered as people in Chechnya] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191206140826/http://www.rus-obr.ru/ru-web/5974 |date=2019-12-06 }} Russian Observer, 12 March 2010</ref>\n\n=== Letter of Orthodox Christian Priest ===\nFather Zachary from Saint Michael the Archangel Church in Grozny has sent a letter to [[Alexiy II]]:\n{{quotation|It is impossible to describe by human words those horror life, which we live here. It is life in hell, between arrogant evil and total lawless: Chechens do not want to work peacefully together with people of other nations, they prefer to live by robberies, thefts, kidnapping. Most of them are armed, they take and rob everything they can, at home and during production. Slave trade has become typical in Chechnya, they make business of anything. And we, the Orthodox people, have to wait our destiny of slaves.<ref name=\"trudgenoc\" />}}\n\n== Human rights activists and publicity persons' opinion ==\nSome Russian human rights activists note that crimes against civilians on territories not controlled by Russian Armed Forces went unpunished.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20010702202213/http://www.hro.org/editions/karta/nr3031/chechnia.htm Chechnya: counter-terrorist operation or war?]</ref> Also 1086 PACE Reslolution has condemned the capture of position near civilian settlements by Chechen armed detachments without preliminary warning of civilians on evacuation necessity. All similar crimes of illegal armed groups are included in books published by Memorial, however, authors state that the description of crimes by media is overblown.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.memo.ru/hr/hotpoints/chechen/itogi/index.htm |title=Human rights violation by Chechen Republic of Ichkeriya authorities |access-date=2019-12-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161215185306/http://www.memo.ru/hr/hotpoints/chechen/itogi/Index.htm |archive-date=2016-12-15 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nRussian film director [[Stanislav Govorukhin]] explained the situation in Chechnya during meeting in State Duma on 17 March 1995:\n\n{{quotation|In August and September 1991, about 10 people were killed daily; then the amount reduced to 1\u20132, but it had been happening daily during 3 and half years. The Chechens were robbing, capturing apartments and making slogans: \"Do not buy flats of Vanya and Masha, soon the flats will eventually become yours\". Almost all Russian-speaking population has lost cars. I even do not want to tell how the Russians were bullied and humiliated. The only word that can describe this is \"genocide\". Nobody of human right defenders dared to move a muscle! Of course, I do not want to talk about that again because we talked too much about it. But if Sergey Adamovich Kovalev has screamed in his full own voice that human rights in Chechnya are smashed brutally, directing his message to the world, maybe we would have recovered much sooner and avoided tragedy. I met him twice during commission, and I asked him, \"Do you know anything about human rights violation during three years reign of Dudayev?\" - \"No\", he answered. Well, it is very strange. Moreover, I read today in cyphered messages cossacks' ataman Sharkov statement that in 1991 he had send Kovalyov printed documents and videos on genocide in Chechnya.}}\n\nGeneral Valery Baranov stated that \"sudden exodus of Russian-speaking people from Chechnya was caused by change of political powers and Dudayev's genocidal politics against Russian-speaking residents\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://vpk-news.ru/articles/4741 |title=From military actions to law enforcement functions |access-date=2019-12-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191206130730/https://vpk-news.ru/articles/4741 |archive-date=2019-12-06 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.vpk-news.ru/article.asp?pr_sign=archive.2006.120.articles.conception_01 |title=Baranov V. From military actions to law enforcement functions // Military Industry Courier, No. 4 (120). 1\u20147 February 2006 |access-date=6 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090318070418/http://www.vpk-news.ru/article.asp?pr_sign=archive.2006.120.articles.conception_01 |archive-date=18 March 2009 |url-status=dead }}</ref> However, many public persons and publicists were denying facts of genocide of Russians made by Dudayev's regime. In 2009 [[Valeriya Novodvorskaya]] called the facts about genocide of Russians \"typical lie of Kremlin\". In 2012 she stated that no one Russian was killed in Chechnya, but mass migration took place because Russians did not understand Chechens, did not want to stay them because of their \"commies' mind\" and the genocide of Russians was caused by Russian Army actions.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://vnovodvorskaia.livejournal.com/947908.html#cutid1 |title=Genocide \u2013 Holocaust |access-date=2019-12-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170625105456/http://vnovodvorskaia.livejournal.com/947908.html#cutid1 |archive-date=2017-06-25 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n{{quotation|That was all typical lie and Kremlin's fairy-tales which were told during [[First Chechen War]] and were going to assure that Russians were killed or expelled... I was there! First Deputy of Dudayev was Russian, his minister was Russian, first victims were old Russian people from five-stored houses \u2013 they refused to evacuate to Chechen villages. Russians bombed them firsts, they were first victims. So I cannot remember more arrogant lie than \"genocide of Russians in Chechnya\", even if we include [[Joseph Goebbels]]' propaganda.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://rutube.ru/tracks/3113020.html |title=Novodvorskaya statements on genocide in Chechnya |access-date=2019-12-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120311044021/http://rutube.ru/tracks/3113020.html |archive-date=2012-03-11 |url-status=live }}</ref>}}\n\n=== Appeal of former refugees to President of Russia ===\nIn 2005 a group of Russian refugees from Grozny sent an appeal to President of Russia and asked him to equal their rights with Chechens, to confirm fact of ethnic cleansing in Chechnya in 1991\u20131994, blaming Kremlin in trying not to reveal the facts of non-Chechen people persecutions and requiring for the same compensation as for returned ones to Chechnya. According to several sources, Chechen authorities have paid a huge compensation for those who returned to Chechnya.<ref name=\":12\" />\n\n=== Politicians and journalists' reaction ===\nIn July 2000 [[President of Russia]] [[Vladimir Putin]] said, \"Last years we saw large-scale genocide of Russian nation and Russian-speaking population in Chechnya. Unfortunately, nobody dared to move a muscle after that\".<ref>{{cite web  |url= http://kremlin.ru/events/president/transcripts/24166|title=Interview of Vladimir Putin|author=[[Marek Halter]]|work=[[Paris Match]]|date=2000-07-06|publisher=[[Kremlin.ru]]|accessdate=2015-08-17|language=ru|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20150817204131/http://kremlin.ru/events/president/transcripts/24166|archivedate=2015-08-17}}</ref> In 2002 Putin at the meeting with Chechen community representatives noted that [[Aslan Maskhadov]]'s reign led to genocide against other nations was arranged in Chechnya, total collapse of social and spiritual areas of life, economic collapse and hunger.<ref>[http://www.mid.ru/bl.nsf/218603db65cac2d343256ac50038d63e/2723802722b3079143256c6e002a40e0?OpenDocument President of Russia Vladimir Putin at the meeting of Chechen community, 10 November 2002] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150215210115/http://www.mid.ru/bl.nsf/218603db65cac2d343256ac50038d63e/2723802722b3079143256c6e002a40e0?OpenDocument |date=15 February 2015 }} (Russian Ministry of Foreign Affairs)</ref> In November 2000 [[Anna Politkovskaya]] had to answer the question on genocide of Russians in Chechnya, which was published in Novaya Gazeta:<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://politkovskaya.novayagazeta.ru/pub/2000/2000-096.shtml |title=Anna Politkovskaya answers your questions |access-date=2019-12-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190523050045/http://politkovskaya.novayagazeta.ru/pub/2000/2000-096.shtml |archive-date=2019-05-23 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n{{quotation|'''Kirill''': [...] Just one question: why cannot I remember any of your articles during 1991-1994 years when genocide of Russians was taking place in Chechnya?<br />\n'''Politkovskaya''': Dear Kirill! In 1991-1994 I did not have any physical opportunity to study the problem of Russians genocide in Chechnya. However, the genocide of Chechens nowadays is obvious, it is performed by military and the Chechens themselves. Many times I tried to explain myself many facts I witnessed, thinking of it as a regrettable case or the stupidity of the performer, but every time I failed, because there is a system of Chechen exterminating in Russia. I cannot explain the happening events in another way. Helas.}}\n\nRussian NTV channel journalist [[Yelena Masyuk]], who was captured by Chechens, in 2009 told that she had not seen any signs of Russians genocide, on which a lot of people were talking.<ref>[http://echo.msk.ru/programs/albac/640854-echo/ Total Albatz show] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191206130652/https://echo.msk.ru/programs/albac/640854-echo/ |date=2019-12-06 }}, [[Echo of Moscow]], 13 December 2009</ref> Her statements are disproved by another journalist, Timofey Borisov from [[Rossiyskaya Gazeta]], who mentioned many facts of genocide.<ref>[http://www.rg.ru/anons/arc_2001/0905/1.shtm Dairy of a Chechen girl] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304222203/http://rg.ru/anons/arc_2001/0905/1.shtm |date=2016-03-04 }}, Timofey Borisov</ref> M.K.Kokorin stated in the same newspaper that the list of assaults confirms official genocidal policy against Russians in Chechnya,<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.rg.ru/anons/arc_2000/0401/4.htm |title=If we do not stop bandits in Chechnya, we will have to fight near our homes |access-date=2019-12-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191206130640/https://rg.ru/anons/arc_2000/0401/4.htm |archive-date=2019-12-06 |url-status=live }}</ref> but publicist Leonid Radzihovsky said that there was not any inter-national conflict between Russians and Chechens because there was not any question on mass return of expelled Russians to houses captured by Chechens.<ref>[http://www.rg.ru/2008/08/05/radzihovskij.html Lobachevsky's diplomacy] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191206130644/https://rg.ru/2008/08/05/radzihovskij.html |date=2019-12-06 }} [[Rossiyskaya Gazeta]], No. 4721, 5 August 2008]</ref>\n\nYuri Shchekochikhin from Novaya Gazeta told once that there were serious contradictions on war perception between \"liberal journalistic\" and law enforcement agencies representatives:<ref>[http://www.novayagazeta.ru/data/2001/45/00.html Covert operations and covert awards] ([https://web.archive.org/web/20100102060631/http://www.novayagazeta.ru/data/2001/45/00.html Archive])</ref>\n\n{{quotation|And, furthermore! They were screaming at me as I was the only Russian journalist, \"Stop puking your lie all over us! Are we the guiltiest ones? Chechen are people, but who are we? Where were you with your human rights when there was total genocide of Russians in Chechnya?! Why did you not resent when Russians have to sell their houses for nothing?!\" I told them about robbed city, they answered, \"Why don't you write how 11 soldiers where hanged upside-down on the Council of Ministers building?\" I told them about Army Captain who had shot from assault rifle four civilians and thought they were guilty of deathes of all but six people from his battalion. They answered me about robbed property brought from trains to Chechen houses.}}\n\n[[Alfred Koch]] told during his lecture in [[Higher School of Economics]] that for unknown reasons nobody had told him that \"in fact, Russian-speaking population of Checheno-Ingushetia was partially slaughtered and partially expelled from territory, where they had been living for centuries\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://slon.ru/russia/gusinskiy_mne_pryamo_govoril_chto_esli_on_ne_polu-467005.xhtml |title=Businessman and ex-reformer Alfred Koch talking about privatization in Russia |access-date=2019-12-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304232707/http://slon.ru/russia/gusinskiy_mne_pryamo_govoril_chto_esli_on_ne_polu-467005.xhtml |archive-date=2016-03-04 |url-status=live }}</ref> At the meeting of State Duma on 20 December 2006 Colonel [[Viktor Alksnis]] blamed Chechen authorities in double morale and told:\n\n{{quotation|I remind that from September 1991 to November 1994 (before first military clashes), according to media, more than 20 thousand Russian civilians, including women, elder people and children, were slaughtered in former Checheno-Ingush ASSR. Ethnic cleansing of Russian population was performed at its territory before first military actions, and more than 250 thousand Russians were expelled.}}\n\nDue to multiple Alksnis' statements on insufficient investigation of Russians genocide in Chechnya he was called by [[Investigative Committee of Russia]] in order to take the stand.<ref>[http://www.newsru.com/russia/27jul2013/sledcomch.html Investigative Committee express interest in getting information on genocide of Russians in Chechnya] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191206130657/https://www.newsru.com/russia/27jul2013/sledcomch.html |date=2019-12-06 }} [[NEWSru.com]] on 27 July 2013</ref> [[Doku Zavgayev]] noted that \"beheading began in Summer 1994, heads were publicly shown on squares, when there had been no Russian troops in the country and First Chechen War had not started yet\" and that ethnic cleansing was directed against multi-ethnic nation of Checheno-Ingush Republic and committed by illegal armed groups led by [[Zelimkhan Yandarbiyev]] and [[Aslan Maskhadov]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://transcript.duma.gov.ru/node/2895/ |title=Transcript of State Duma meeting, 2 October 1996 |access-date=6 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191206130634/http://transcript.duma.gov.ru/node/2895/ |archive-date=6 December 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> In 2013 Russian journalist [[Maksim Shevchenko (journalist)|Maksim Shevchenko]] told that genocide of Russians was \"a legend which has not enough understandable proofs\" and that the first murders of Russians began after bombing Grozny.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.rusnovosti.ru/programms/prog/70601/271620/ |title=Russian News Service, 18:03-18:40 |access-date=2019-12-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141022112008/http://www.rusnovosti.ru/programms/prog/70601/271620/ |archive-date=2014-10-22 |url-status=dead }}</ref> In the same year Sergey Popov told that genocide of Russians was happening from 1990 to 1994 (before the First Chechen War), when more than 200 thousand Russians ran away from the republic.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.stav.aif.ru/society/article/22196 |title=Sergey Popov on North Caucasus Federal District and ethnicity question |access-date=2019-12-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120206092504/http://www.stav.aif.ru/society/article/22196 |archive-date=2012-02-06 |url-status=live }}</ref> [[Akhmed Zakayev]] denied any evidence confirming genocide of Russians in Chechnya of 1990s.<ref>[https://meduza.io/feature/2014/12/11/posle-pervoy-voyny-my-proigrali-mir Akhmed Zakayev says, \"We have lost peace after the first war\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191206130631/https://meduza.io/feature/2014/12/11/posle-pervoy-voyny-my-proigrali-mir |date=2019-12-06 }} [[Meduza]], 11 December 2014, interview made by Ilya Azar</ref> According to [[Sergey Stepashin]], White Book published in Russia is the main proof of Russian people genocide.<ref>[http://teleskop-by.org/2018/09/04/sergej-stepashin-ya-ponimayu-pochemu-putin-vse-bolshe-i-bolshe-obrashhaetsya-k-bogu/ Sergey Stepashin, \"I understand why Putin is talking more and more to the God] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190517042139/http://teleskop-by.org/2018/09/04/sergej-stepashin-ya-ponimayu-pochemu-putin-vse-bolshe-i-bolshe-obrashhaetsya-k-bogu/ |date=2019-05-17 }} Teleskop, 4 September 2018</ref>\n\n=== Russian Parliament members' reaction ===\nThe State Duma members had complicated and controversial opinion on genocide of non-Chechen people in Chechnya. [[Konstantin Borovoy]] denied all statements on genocide of Russians in Chechnya,<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://rutube.ru/video/c9af7ed8934a0cbd66ee7b7edce01832/ |title=Borovoy and Novodvorskaya on genocide of Russians in 1990s |access-date=2019-12-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150215212748/http://rutube.ru/video/c9af7ed8934a0cbd66ee7b7edce01832/ |archive-date=2015-02-15 |url-status=dead }}</ref> while former Department on Federation and Nations Affairs in State Duma [[Mikhail Burlakov]] insisted on the opposite point of view.<ref>[http://www.pzrk.ru/genocide List of Burlakov's articles on genocide of Russians in Chechnya] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090405155050/http://pzrk.ru/genocide |date=2009-04-05 }} {{in lang|ru}}</ref> For example, on 7 December 1994 Burlakov told that a law on defense of Russian population suffered from Chechen radical nationalists is necessary to be passed; Nikolay Lysenko noted that nobody interests what is happening to Russians in Chechnya.\n\n{{quotation|For some reason nobody asks: what is the situation of Russians in Chechnya? According to materials I have, Russians in Chechnya (at least in suburban and rural areas) have already become slaves in agricultural sphere.}}\n\nBurlakov offered to create Duma Committee on the situation with Russians in Chechnya, explaining that the problem of \"Russian slaves serving at plantations in Chechnya\" must be solved, but the results voting were against such Committee creating.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://transcript.duma.gov.ru/node/3126/ |title=Transcript of State Duma meeting, 7 December 1994 |access-date=6 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191206130630/http://transcript.duma.gov.ru/node/3126/ |archive-date=6 December 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Senator [[Evgeny Tarlo]] later compared situation [[War in Donbass|in Donbass]] and Chechnya, reminding that in Chechnya almost all Russians and Russian-speaking people were either killed or expelled\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://4pera.ru/news/picture_of_the_day/razgovor_s_ubiytsey/ |title=Talking to Murderer |access-date=2019-12-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170930083921/http://4pera.ru/news/picture_of_the_day/razgovor_s_ubiytsey/ |archive-date=2017-09-30 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n=== Writers as witnesses ===\nSeveral Russian writers who wrote on events in Chechnya were the direct witnesses of those events, however, their opinions distinguish. Some of writers denied any cases of discrimination of Russians. For example, Polina Zherebtsova, commenting statements on Russian troops entering Chechnya due to genocide of Russians, denied any facts of inter-national brawl:\n\n{{quotation|I was 9 years old in 1994. I understood very little of politics or relationships. I can just tell that the relationships between nations in Grozny and in the district, where my family lived, were peaceful and friendly. People talked nice and helped one another, I can't remember any ethnic feuds.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.krugozormagazine.com/show/Zherebtsova.1404.html|title=\u042d\u0442\u043e \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0443\u043f\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435. \u0413\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0440\u0438\u0442 \u043f\u0438\u0441\u0430\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0438\u0446\u0430 \u041f\u043e\u043b\u0438\u043d\u0430 \u0416\u0435\u0440\u0435\u0431\u0446\u043e\u0432\u0430, \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0435\u0436\u0438\u0432\u0448\u0430\u044f \u0432 \u0413\u0440\u043e\u0437\u043d\u043e\u043c \u0434\u0432\u0435 \u0432\u043e\u0439\u043d\u044b|trans-title=This is crime. A writer Polina Zherebtsova who survived two wars in Grozny speaks|author=\u0415\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0430 \u041c\u0430\u0433\u043b\u0435\u0432\u0430\u043d\u043d\u0430\u044f|date=2012-04-15|website=\u0418\u043d\u0442\u0435\u0440\u043d\u0435\u0442-\u0436\u0443\u0440\u043d\u0430\u043b \u00ab\u041a\u0440\u0443\u0433\u043e\u0437\u043e\u0440\u00bb|accessdate=2017-08-27|language=ru|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170827170351/http://www.krugozormagazine.com/show/Zherebtsova.1404.html|archive-date=2017-08-27|url-status=live}}</ref>}}\n\nTV films director Igor Belyayev, who filmed 14 movies on Chechnya, supported the same version:\n{{quotation|All central newspapers depicted Dudayev as a monster and Grozny as bandits camp where any Russian appearing in the streets was torn apart. However, all of it was made 4 years before war when Grozny was still a peaceful city and Dudayev was the Soviet general. All this noise was made by press, but it is hard to say whether it was ordered or it was stupid mistake.<ref>{{cite book|author=Igor Belyayev|title=Documents spectacle. Revelations of television|trans-title=\u0421\u043f\u0435\u043a\u0442\u0430\u043a\u043b\u044c \u0434\u043e\u043a\u0443\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0442\u043e\u0432. \u041e\u0442\u043a\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f \u0442\u0435\u043b\u0435\u0432\u0438\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f|location=Moscow|publisher=Geleos|year=2005|page=[https://archive.org/details/spektakldokument0000beli/page/286 286]|isbn=5-8189-0403-2|url=https://archive.org/details/spektakldokument0000beli/page/286}}</ref>}}\n\nHowever, Yuri Kondratyev from Grozny states in his books, which won several awards (Teneta-2002, Memoirs Category) that Russians were people of \"second class\" in Chechnya.<ref>[https://www.kp.ru/daily/23611/46725/ Russians of \"second class\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191206145130/https://www.kp.ru/daily/23611/46725/ |date=2019-12-06 }} [[Komsomolskaya Pravda]], 15 November 2005</ref> He told about events of 1991 in Grozny in his book \"Grozny. Several days\":\n\n{{quotation|Krushchevka of my parents was in the center of the city at Partizanskaya St. against Republican Art Foundation. Once they saw a scene from the 4th floor of the building, a scene, which  became typical in the city. Several Russian guys were walking aside Art Foundation building when a black Volga passed and stopped near them. Several armed Chechens left Volga and shot the guys at point blank range from assault guns, then sat back at the car and slowly left the area. That was not mafia showdown, we had never had it. Then my parents understood the essence of \"independent Ichkeriya\". Both of them saw the war and fought, but this scene shocked them by its senseless brutality.}}\n\n== Number of victims evaluation ==\nIn July 1999 the Russian Ministry of Nations Affairs disclosed that during the years nine years since 1991, more than 21,000 Russian civilians{{Clarify|reason=When we say Russian civilians do we mean it in the verified by NGO civilians sense or the patriotic resistance civilian resistance type of Russian?|date=December 2019}} lost their lives. Property losses were estimated to be at least 100,000 domiciles destroyed or commandeered by native civilians. At least 46 thousand individuals had their property and passports confiscated.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ng.ru/regions/2003-05-23/4_kazak.html |title=Displacement of Russians in Chechnya is still going on due to federal officials' indifference |access-date=2009-08-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090531100704/http://www.ng.ru/regions/2003-05-23/4_kazak.html |archive-date=2009-05-31 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20010718065203/http://www.cdi.org/russia/johnson/3376.html Itar-Tass: Over 21,000 Russians Killed in Chechnya Since 1991] // Center for Defense Information</ref><ref>[http://www.vesti.ru/doc.html?id=16758 Vladimir Putin: Russia will not start negotiations with Chechen terrorists and bandits] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090318070746/http://www.vesti.ru/doc.html?id=16758 |date=2009-03-18 }} [[Russia-1|Rossiya Channel]], 19 December 2002</ref>\n\nAccording to historic population data, there were 269,130 Russians in Checheno-Ingush ASSR in 1989 (24.8%) and there were 24,382 Russians in Chechen Republic of Russian Federation in 2010 (1.9%).<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ethno-kavkaz.narod.ru/rnchechenia.html |title=Chechnya population data |access-date=2019-12-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191013234204/http://www.ethno-kavkaz.narod.ru/rnchechenia.html |archive-date=2019-10-13 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n== Accountability of perpetrators ==\nPutin's statement on human rights violations during counter-terrorism operations in the Northern Caucasus region of Russia pledged quick investigation into genocide in Chechnya cases and placed responsibility for these and other crimes on criminal \"Dudayev \u2013 Maskhadov regime\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.rg.ru/oficial/from_min/prezident/264.htm |title=Information provided by President of Russia Press Service |access-date=2019-12-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305013343/http://rg.ru/oficial/from_min/prezident/264.htm |archive-date=2016-03-05 |url-status=live }}</ref> Despite multiple evidences of murders, robberies and other crimes committed by Chechen bandits, {{Citation needed|date=December 2019}}Russian law enforcement and justice agencies rarely tried to complete these cases. There was nohigh-profile cases or lawsuits against Chechen Republic of Ichkeriya authorities, the crimes committed by Ichkeriyan bandits were not investigated properly. Most of terrorists were killed during counter-terrorist operations. However, several noted lawyers expressed their opinion on non-Chechen population genocide: for example, Igor Kiselev, the former Acting Prosecutor of Chechen Republic and the official of Prosecutor General of Russia in the Northern Caucasus told Rossiyskaya Gazeta on the legitimacy and law and order in [[Chechen Republic of Ichkeriya]]:<ref>[http://www.rg.ru/anons/arc_1999/1126/22.htm Blood feud is canceled] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090715082940/http://www.rg.ru/anons/arc_1999/1126/22.htm |date=2009-07-15 }} [[Rossiyskaya Gazeta]], 1999</ref>\n\n{{quotation|Laws of self-described Ichkeriya and policy of her leaders lead to double standards. Outside we see almost European Constitution with guarantees of main rights and freedoms of a human and a civilian, rule of international law declaration, nice postulates on movement to common and fair world based on universal human values. Inside we see terrorist enclave where robberies, violence, slave trade and slave labor flourish, where drugs and counterfeit money production is taking place and where civilians of non-Chechen ethnicity are extinguished. Today somebody is worried by stream of refugees from Chechnya caused by military actions, but what should we do to mass emigration of Russians, Nogai people, Dargins, Avars and nations of Dagestan? During last years more than a half of Republic population and Russian citizens have left the republic, saving their lives and property.}}\n\nThe Criminal Code of Ichkeriya, which was published in Ichkeriya newspaper (6 September 1999) was the translation and copy of Republic of Sudan Criminal Code, according to experts: all the fines were fixed in Sudan pounds, paying for blood spilling was expressed in camels (100 camels for murder of a capable and free human).<ref>[http://www.bekkin.ru/index.php?rub=8&art=28 R. Bekkin, V. Bobrovnikov. Northern Caucasus is not a kingdom of noble outlaws] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181127152431/http://www.bekkin.ru/index.php?rub=8&art=28 |date=2018-11-27 }} // Tatarsky Mir, 2003, No. 19 (December). p.8]</ref>\n\nOn 1 February 1995 a criminal case was opened by Prosecutor General of Russia against Dzhokhar Dudayev (Articles 64-A, 70\u20131, 133-1 part 1, 74 part 3 of Criminal Code of RSFSR). Dudayev was accused of inter-ethnic hatred:\n\n{{quotation|Due to policy conducted by D.M.Dudayev and his assistants in Chechen Republic the inter-social, inter-ethnic, inter-religious hatred and feud has appeared and led to the frank discrimination of Russian people, which are suffering from insults, reprisal threats, direct violence, degradation, illegitimate property confiscation and forced migration from republic. Dudayev's actions are related to part 3, Article 74 Criminal Code of RSFSR.<ref name=\"white book\" />}}\n\nHowever, Dudayev was killed on 21 April 1996 near Gekhi-Chu village (30&nbsp;km from Grozny) by Russian secret services. In the end of 1999 the General Prosecutor of Russia ordered Aslan Maskhadov immediately visit Russian law enforcement agency and provide all information related on Russians genocide in Chechen Republic after finding mass graves in Chechnya.<ref>[http://www.lenta.ru/vojna/1999/12/30/maskhadov/ Prosecutor General of Russia shall accuse Maskhadov of genocide of Russians in Chechnya] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160312221040/https://lenta.ru/vojna/1999/12/30/maskhadov/ |date=2016-03-12 }} {{in lang|ru}}</ref> However, this case did not receive any public judicial reporting, Maskhadov did not appear to give information and was eventually killed on 8 March 2005 by FSB forces in Tolstoy-Yurt village (Grozny rural district), therefore investigation of crimes was not performed.\n\nFormer Mufti of Chechnya [[Akhmad Kadyrov]], who requires publicly to kill Russians in Chechnya, was later pardoned and was not held responsible for his calls to [[jihad]] against Russian. Later he was appointed as President of Chechnya by Vladimir Putin and killed on 9 May 2004. Next Day Putin signed a decree on Akhmad Kadyrov's name perpetuation in Grozny (naming the square in Grozny and school in Centoroy, where Kadyrov learned). President recommended to Moscow local authorities to think on the similar perpetuation in the capital, and 3 and a half months later one of the streets was renamed, despite locals' protests.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.kasparov.ru/material.php?id=47159C56D411F |title=Garry Kasparov says, \"Anna &#91;Politkovskaya&#93; proved that authorities and order did not cross at the same places in modern Russia |access-date=2019-12-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180723215458/http://www.kasparov.ru/material.php?id=47159C56D411F |archive-date=2018-07-23 |url-status=live }}</ref> The appeal of public persons to Russian authorities with requiring to recognize legally the genocide of Russians in Chechnya was left without any reaction.<ref name=Appeal/>\n\n=== Ramzes Goychaev criminal case ===\nIn 2001 a Chechen person Ramzes Goychaev was initially accused by the court of Russians genocide in Chechnya in 1997-1999 (Article 357 of Russian Criminal Code). According to prosecution information, Goychaev's gang has murdered 10 Russian people in Chervlyonnaya (Shelkovsky District, Republic of Chechnya)<ref>[http://news.ng.ru/2001/04/18/987592126.html Chechen terrorist Goychaev sentenced to death] ([https://web.archive.org/web/20090531203613/http://news.ng.ru/2001/04/18/987592126.html Archive]) // [[Nezavisimaya gazeta]], 18 April 2001.</ref> Despite the fact that accusation of genocide was used for the first time in history of Russian justice, the court did not plead Goyachev guilty of genocide because of genocide understanding as \"the crime against world and humanity safety\".<ref>[http://www.kommersant.ru/doc.aspx?fromsearch=33b541f4-4ee9-4cf3-8276-ba78dd600e06&docsid=290776 Bandits were killing Russians] // Kommersant, \u2116 206 (2336), 10 November 2001] {{in lang|ru}}'</ref> However, several murders were enough reason to sentence Goychaev to death penalty, which was finally replaced by [[life sentence]].<ref>[http://www.gazeta.ru/2001/04/18/pervyjsmertn.shtml The first death sentence for five years] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191031190749/https://www.gazeta.ru/2001/04/18/pervyjsmertn.shtml |date=2019-10-31 }} // [[Gazeta.Ru]], 18 April 2001 {{in lang|ru}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Novye Aldi massacre]]\n* [[:ru:\u041f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u0430 \u0447\u0435\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0435\u043a\u0430 \u0432 \u0427\u0435\u0447\u043d\u0435 \u0432 \u0445\u043e\u0434\u0435 \u0412\u0442\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0439 \u0447\u0435\u0447\u0435\u043d\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u0432\u043e\u0439\u043d\u044b|Human rights during Second Chechen War]]\n* [[:ru:\u0420\u0443\u0441\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0435 \u0432 \u0427\u0435\u0447\u043d\u0435|Russians in Chechnya]]\n* [[Borozdinovskaya operation]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n== Literature ==\n* {{cite book|author=Romanov, P. V.|title=Chechnya. White Book|trans-title=\u0427\u0435\u0447\u043d\u044f. \u0411\u0435\u043b\u0430\u044f \u043a\u043d\u0438\u0433\u0430|url=https://archive.org/details/kgbivlast0000bobk|url-status=dead|location=Moscow|year=2000|publisher=[[RIA Novosti]], Rosinformcenter|isbn=5-900328-44-9|url-access=registration}}\n* {{cite book|author=Surkov A. P.|title=Chechnya in Flame of Separatism|trans-title=\u0427\u0435\u0447\u043d\u044f \u0432 \u043f\u043b\u0430\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0438 \u0441\u0435\u043f\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0442\u0438\u0437\u043c\u0430|url=http://www.lib.unn.ru/php/details.php?DocId=29469&DB=1|location=\u0421\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0442\u043e\u0432|publisher=Povolzhye academic state service publishing house|year=1998}}\n* {{cite book|author=Yuri Kondratyev|title=Grozny. Several days|trans-title=\u0413\u0440\u043e\u0437\u043d\u044b\u0439. \u041d\u0435\u0441\u043a\u043e\u043b\u044c\u043a\u043e \u0434\u043d\u0435\u0439|series=\u0412\u043e\u0441\u043f\u043e\u043c\u0438\u043d\u0430\u043d\u0438\u044f \u043e \u0413\u0440\u043e\u0437\u043d\u043e\u043c (Memory of Grozny)|url=http://conrad2001.narod.ru/russian/grozny.htm|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071215134142/http://conrad2001.narod.ru/russian/grozny.htm|url-status=dead|archive-date=2007-12-15}}\n* {{cite book|author=Dmitry Sokolov-Mitrich|title=Non-Tajik girls, non-Chechen boys|trans-title=\u041d\u0435\u0442\u0430\u0434\u0436\u0438\u043a\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0435 \u0434\u0435\u0432\u043e\u0447\u043a\u0438. \u041d\u0435\u0447\u0435\u0447\u0435\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0435 \u043c\u0430\u043b\u044c\u0447\u0438\u043a\u0438|publisher=Yauza-Press|year=2007|pages=320|isbn=978-5-903339-45-7}}\n* {{cite book|author=[[Paul Khlebnikov]]|title=Talking to Barbarian|trans-title=\u0420\u0430\u0437\u0433\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0440 \u0441 \u0432\u0430\u0440\u0432\u0430\u0440\u043e\u043c|pages=288|year=2005|publisher=Detective-Press|isbn=5-89935-057-1}}\n* {{cite journal|author=Vladimir Zykov|title=Blood and Dust|trans-title=\u041a\u0440\u043e\u0432\u044c \u0438 \u043f\u044b\u043b\u044c|editor=Introduction by Igor Shafarevich, \"The voice from total darkness|publisher=Nash Sovremennik|issue=11|year=1996|location=Moscow|language=ru}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://reeed.ru/lib/books/dnevnik_mirnogo_zhitelya_goroda_groznogo/|title=\"\u0414\u043d\u0435\u0432\u043d\u0438\u043a \u043c\u0438\u0440\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0436\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044f \u0433\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0434\u0430 \u0413\u0440\u043e\u0437\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e\" \u0413\u0440\u0438\u0447\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0430 \u041d. \u0413.|trans-title=Diary of a Grozny Civilian N.G.Grichanov|date=2011}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://www.litsovet.ru/index.php/material.read?material_id=310875|title=\"\u041d\u0430\u0441 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u0430\u043b\u0430 \u0420\u043e\u0434\u0438\u043d\u0430\"|trans-title=We were betrayed by Motherland|date=2010|author=Konstantin Semenov}} (original name of book is \"Grozny Novel\" \u2014 \u00ab\u0413\u0440\u043e\u0437\u043d\u0435\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0440\u043e\u043c\u0430\u043d\u00bb)\n* {{cite web|url=http://www.litsovet.ru/index.php/material.read?material_id=368900|title=\"\u0413\u0440\u043e\u0437\u043d\u0435\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0435 \u043c\u0438\u0440\u0430\u0436\u0438\"|trans-title=Grozny Mirages|date=2011|author=Konstantin Semenov}}\n\n== External links ==\n*{{cite web|url=https://www.refworld.org/docid/469f38d12.html| title=Chronology of events in Chechnya|publisher=Minorities at Risk| year=2004}}\n\n{{Chechen wars|state=expanded}}\n\n[[Category:1991 establishments in Russia]]\n[[Category:1994 disestablishments in Russia]]\n[[Category:Anti-Russian sentiment]]\n[[Category:Chechen Republic of Ichkeria]]\n[[Category:Chechen\u2013Russian conflict]]\n[[Category:Human rights abuses in Russia]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Violent actions and segregation between 1990 and 2005}}\n{{Campaignbox First Chechen War|state=expanded}}\n{{multiple issues|{{Original research|date=December 2019}}{{Accuracy dispute|date=December 2019}}}}\n'''[[Anti-Russian sentiment|Anti-Russian violence]] was recorded in [[Chechnya]]''' ({{lang-ru|\u042d\u0442\u043d\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0435 \u0447\u0438\u0441\u0442\u043a\u0438 \u0432 \u0427\u0435\u0447\u043d\u0435}}). The violent acts were committed against [[Russians|Russian]] and non-Chechen civilians in Chechnya from 1991 to 1994. Tens of thousands of Russians left Chechnya.\n\n== Background ==\nDuring the 1990s, Chechen leaders accused the Russian government of attempting genocide against the ethnic Chechen population.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.inosmi.ru/text/translation/140373.html|title=The deepest Western silence as the reply to Chechen nation's genocide|date=2002-03-25|work=[[Le Figaro]]|publisher=inosmi.ru|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090318010733/http://www.inosmi.ru/text/translation/140373.html|archivedate=2009-03-18}} [http://www.chechenpress.info/news/2004/01/02/03.shtml] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191206130631/http://www.chechenpress.info/news/2004/01/02/03.shtml|date=2019-12-06}}</ref> Some politicians{{Clarify|reason=|date=December 2019}} used these terms to describe the actions of both sides.{{Citation needed|date=December 2019}} In a 2006 interview, Yuri Ivanov, a former member of the Russian government, claimed to have seen camps in Chechnya between 1993 and 1995 where hundreds of thousands of Russians, Greeks, and religious minorities were interned in Chechnya in what he described as a genocide.<ref>[http://www.echo.msk.ru/programs/exit/42883/ Echo of Moscow, radio show Ischem Vykhod (Looking for Exit), theme \"Is there the independent justice in Russia] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191206130639/https://echo.msk.ru/programs/exit/42883/|date=2019-12-06}}, 12 April 2006</ref>\n\nIn 2010 [[Alexander Khloponin]] said that the migration of the Russian-speaking population from Chechnya to other regions of Russia in the 1990s was due primarily to economic pressures.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rg.ru/2010/05/27/hloponin.html|title=\u0427\u0430\u0441 \u0432\u043e\u0439\u043d\u0435, \u043d\u043e \u0432\u0440\u0435\u043c\u044f \u2014 \u0436\u0438\u0437\u043d\u0438|trans-title=An hour for war, the time for life|publisher=[[Rossiyskaya gazeta]]|date=2010-05-27|access-date=2019-12-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191206131655/https://rg.ru/2010/05/27/hloponin.html|archive-date=2019-12-06|url-status=live}} No. 5192 (113)'</ref>. According to a report published by the [[Moscow Helsinki Group]] in 2006, while many former Soviet republics saw the mass emigration of Russian speakers to Russia, only in Chechnya was this emigration primarily spurred by anti-Russian sentiment and the threat of violence.<ref name=\":2\">[http://www.mhg.ru/files/knigi/prksen1.pdf Opposing xenophobia and ethnic discrimination courses] (https://web.archive.org/web/20090611185909/http://www.mhg.ru/files/knigi/prksen1.pdf Archive])</ref> Local Chechen attitudes increasingly blamed Russia for their economic and political troubles, and viewed ethnic Russians as hostile \"colonizers\" of Chechnya.<ref name=\":2\" /> \n\nRussian commentators have described the animosity between Chechens and Russians as a conflict that has persisted since Russia's attempts to consolidate the territory into its empire in the 18th century.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ng.ru/regions/2002-05-23/5_leeder.html|title=\u0421\u0435\u0433\u043e\u0434\u043d\u044f\u0448\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u0441\u043e\u0431\u044b\u0442\u0438\u044f \u2014 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0434\u043e\u043b\u0436\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u041a\u0430\u0432\u043a\u0430\u0437\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u0432\u043e\u0439\u043d\u044b|trans-title=Today events are the continuation of the Caucasus War|publisher=Nezavisimaya gazeta|date=2002-05-23|access-date=2019-12-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191206130629/http://www.ng.ru/regions/2002-05-23/5_leeder.html|archive-date=2019-12-06|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nA [[Central Intelligence Agency|CIA]] report in 1992 documents that as of its publication, roughly 50,000 ethnic Russians had left Chechnya due to fears of violence<ref>[https://www.cia.gov/library/readingroom/docs/DOC_0000837999.pdf The punished peoples: a primer on Russia's North Caucasus] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170913183802/https://www.cia.gov/library/readingroom/docs/DOC_0000837999.pdf |date=2017-09-13 }} CIA's Directorate of Intelligence file, 2 April 1992</ref>\n\nAccording to [[Soviet Census (1989)|All-Union Census of 1989]], there were 1,270,429 residents of  [[Checheno-Ingush Autonomous Soviet Socialist Republic|Checheno-Ingush ASSR]], including 734,501 Chechens, 293,771 Russians, 163,762 Ingushes, 14,824 Armenians, 14,824 Tatars, 12,637 Nogai people etc.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://demoscope.ru/weekly/ssp/rus_nac_89.php?reg=49|title=Soviet Census 1989|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190403210621/http://www.demoscope.ru/weekly/ssp/rus_nac_89.php?reg=49|archive-date=2019-04-03|access-date=2019-12-06}}</ref>. The population of Chechnya was 1,100,000 residents<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ethno-kavkaz.narod.ru/rnchechenia.html|title=Ethno-Caucasus. Population of Chechnya districts in 1989|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191013234204/http://www.ethno-kavkaz.narod.ru/rnchechenia.html|archive-date=2019-10-13|access-date=2019-12-06}}</ref>, including 397,000 people of [[Grozny]] (210,000 Russians)<ref name=\"Appeal\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.obraschenie.front.ru/|title=\u041e\u0431\u0440\u0430\u0449\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u043e\u0431 \u043e\u0444\u0438\u0446\u0438\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u043e\u043c \u043f\u0440\u0438\u0437\u043d\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0438 \u0413\u0435\u043d\u043e\u0446\u0438\u0434\u0430 \u0440\u0443\u0441\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0445 \u0432 \u0427\u0435\u0447\u043d\u0435|trans-title=Appeal on official recognition of Russian people genocide in Chechnya|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070415231013/http://www.obraschenie.front.ru/|archivedate=2007-04-15|accessdate=2007-05-05}}</ref>. \n\n== Oppression of Russian people during Dudayev regime ==\nAccording to [[Izvestiya]] newspaper, the persecutions of Russian began in 1990s, starting with threatening letters telling Russians to leave in 1990, followed by the disappearances of Russian girls and reports of Russian men being assaulted.<ref name=\":12\">[https://archive.today/20120530021036/www.izvestia.ru/russia/article1092129/ Forgotten Genocide]. [[Izvestiya]], 28 January 2005</ref> Russian government officials have described the ensuing events as a genocide, and described various anti-Russian slogans attributed to Chechens which called for the expulsion and/or enslavement of Russians.<ref name=\":02\">[http://www.specnaz.ru/article/?1267 Gates of Thunder] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170913231033/http://www.specnaz.ru/article/?1267|date=2017-09-13}} Spetsnaz Rossii, issue 5 (14), May 2008 {{in lang|ru}}</ref><ref>[http://svpressa.ru/society/article/66089/ Return to Ingushetia] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191206130707/https://svpressa.ru/society/article/66089/|date=2019-12-06}} ID Svobodnaya Pressa, 12 June 2013,</ref>\n\n[[BBC Russian Service]] describes local Communist Party official Vitaly Kutsenko as having been the first casualty of anti-Russian violence leading up to the [[First Chechen War]] when he was assaulted by supporters of [[Dzhokhar Dudayev]] and members of National Congress of Chechen People. Conflicting reports allege that either Kutsenko was thrown out of a window of his office, or died from falling after trying to escape out a window.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/russian/russia/2009/12/091210_chechnya_war_history|title=\u041f\u0435\u0440\u0432\u0430\u044f \u0447\u0435\u0447\u0435\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0430\u044f: \u043f\u0443\u0442\u044c \u043a \u0432\u043e\u0439\u043d\u0435|author=\u0410\u0440\u0442\u0435\u043c \u041a\u0440\u0435\u0447\u0435\u0442\u043d\u0438\u043a\u043e\u0432|date=2009-12-10|website=BBC News Russian Service|lang=ru|accessdate=2019-12-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171025105730/http://www.bbc.com/russian/russia/2009/12/091210_chechnya_war_history|archive-date=2017-10-25|url-status=live}}</ref>  According to Russian political commentators, the lack of action from the Soviet government in response to this assault further emboldened Chechen forces to carry out violence against Russians.<ref>[http://www.kommersant.ru/doc.aspx?fromsearch=ac89d082-b347-4736-85b9-eb7ff6a28869&docsid=281761 Day of Banditism, Terrorism and Arbitrariness] Kommersant, No. 161 (2291), 6 September 2001]</ref><ref>[http://www.rg.ru/2009/10/08/edelev.html Checkists capture Staff] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191206131217/https://rg.ru/2009/10/08/edelev.html |date=2019-12-06 }} [[Rossiyskaya Gazeta]], No. 5013 (189)</ref>. \n\nThe residents of Assinovskaya, Sunzhensky Disctict, Chechnya have sent open letter to President of Russia [[Boris Yeltsin]], in which they named all the cases of assaults on Russian people and murders of them. According to the letter, 26 Russian families had been murdered since August 1996 and more than 52 households were kidnapped by the Chechen forces.<ref name=\"trudgenoc\">[http://conrad2001.narod.ru/russian/genocide/genocide_8.htm Vladimir Yanchenkov. Documentary evidence of genocide of Russians in Mashakdov's Ichkeriya] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150725204149/http://conrad2001.narod.ru/russian/genocide/genocide_8.htm|date=2015-07-25}}, Trud, 17 February 2000</ref> Another appeal made by 50 thousand residents of Naursky and Shelkovsky Districts was mentioned in a book published by Rosinformcenter.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.fsb.ru/history/book/white/white.html |title=Archived copy |access-date=2019-12-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080419125844/http://www.fsb.ru/history/book/white/white.html |archive-date=2008-04-19 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref name=\"white book\">{{Cite web |url=http://conrad2001.narod.ru/russian/library/books/wh_book_3/wh_book_3-6.htm |title=\"Chechnya. White Book.\" Moscow, 2000. RIA Novosti, Rosinformcenter |access-date=2019-12-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150724030428/http://conrad2001.narod.ru/russian/library/books/wh_book_3/wh_book_3-6.htm |archive-date=2015-07-24 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nPeople fleeing Chechnya could not get refugee status because, according to Russian laws, the refugee status could be offered only during migration to another country, therefore those people were considered as \"internally displaced persons\".<ref>[http://www.trud.ru/issue/article.php?id=200002170300502 Outcasts in Homeland] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191206130658/http://www.trud.ru/issue/article.php%3Fid%3D200002170300502|date=2019-12-06}} Trud // No.30, 17 February 2000]</ref> According to ethnologist Valery Tishkov, almost all non-Chechen (mostly Russian) population was expelled or exterminated during war by locals; about 200 thousand people have to run away from Grozny, however, Russian authorities and world community were completely indifferent to their problems.<ref>[http://www.valerytishkov.ru/cntnt/publikacii3/lekcii2/video/chechenska1.html Chechen War. Anthropologist' view, part 1 by Valery Tishkov] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190522033149/http://www.valerytishkov.ru/cntnt/publikacii3/lekcii2/video/chechenska1.html|date=2019-05-22}} (see 85:00)</ref> During 1990s a large inscription reading \"Russians, do not leave us, we need slaves and prostitutes\" appeared at the entry of the city of Grozny.<ref>{{cite web|last=\u0421\u043e\u0448\u0438\u043d|first=\u042e\u0440\u0438\u0439|publisher=\u0418\u043d\u0444\u043e\u0440\u043c\u0430\u0446\u0438\u043e\u043d\u043d\u043e-\u0430\u043d\u0430\u043b\u0438\u0442\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u044d\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0442\u0440\u043e\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u0436\u0443\u0440\u043d\u0430\u043b \u00ab\u0424\u0430\u043a\u0442\u00bb #23|url=http://www.fact.ru/www/arhiv23bez-2.htm|title=\u0411\u043e\u043b\u044c\u0448\u043e\u0439 \u043a\u0430\u0432\u043a\u0430\u0437\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0442\u0443\u043f\u0438\u043a|lang=ru|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110706102600/http://www.fact.ru/www/arhiv23bez-2.htm|archivedate=2011-07-06}}</ref>.\n\nOn 17 June 1993 Council of Nations of [[Supreme Soviet of Russia]] adopted statement \"Due to the situation in Chechen Republic\", in which it was stated that the policy of the Chechen authorities led to \"serious deterioration of different nations\", some of which \"are expelled over the borders of republic and have to leave places, where they and their ancestors had been living together with Chechens and Ingushes for many generations\"<ref>Statement of Council of Nations of Supreme Soviet of Russia, 17 June 1993, No. 5205-I \"\"Due to the situation in Chechen Republic\"</ref>. But in October 1994 President of Chechen Republic of Ichkeriya Dzhokhar Dudayev claimed during an interview with [[Interfax]]  that reports of persecution of non-Chechen people in Ichkeriya was simply Russian propaganda, and highlighted proclamations made by his government against the persecution of Russians.<ref name=\"white book\" />\n\nIn 2006, [[Ziyad Sabsabi]] the Chechen Republic Prime Minister Deputy denied the occurrence of a genocide against Russians in Ichkeriya in 1992 and 1993, stating that\n{{quotation|We will not and are not going to silence [that]. However, I want to note that there was no genocide of particular nation: Jews, Armenians, Russians, Ukrainians etc. lived in Chechnya. But I can assure you, the victims of illegitimate armed groups were also Chechens, which suffered from them not less than Russians.<ref>[http://www.echo.msk.ru/programs/razvorot/48128/ Anniversary of Russian troops entering Chechnya. Current situation] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191206130639/https://echo.msk.ru/programs/razvorot/48128/ |date=2019-12-06 }}. Razvorot radio show, 11 December 2016, [[Echo of Moscow]]</ref>}}\n\n=== Examples ===\nOn 18 February 1992 an appeal of a woman who used to live in Grozny sooner was published. She informed on different criminal actions against Russian residents of the city<ref name=\"white book\" />: \n{{quotation|[Chechens] threw us out during the middle of school year and did not leave us neither vacation, nor tickets or compensation. Then they started bullying children: for example, in a school with majority of Russian children bottles with mercury have been thrown, and girls were afraid to walk in the streets because indigenous youngsters pursued them and tried to kidnap them.\n\nThe situation is unbearable in transport and shops. One can't even buy bread without listening insults or provocations. Dudayev's gang of youngsters tried to enter our apartment at night (before elections), they were sliding daggers and screaming.}}\n\nAfter the military coup d'\u00e9tat by Dudayev total change of locals' attitude to military had changed: armed people have captured and destroyed internal troops regiment, aviation training regiment, anti-aircraft signals regiment. The assaults were performed by personnel of \"Cheborz\" company led by [[Shamil Basayev]]. Part of weapons and vehicles, all signal devices, car parts and other necessaries  have been stolen, and at the same time mass exodus of Russian-speaking population began<ref name=\"white book\"/>. [[Boris Yeltsin]] paid a lot of attention to that situation and mentioned in his statement from 19 October 1991:\n{{quotation|... during last weeks peaceful land of Checheno-Ingushetia turned into arena of mass riots and armed conflicts followed by capturing of government agencies, pogroms, misconducts and death of people... All actions taken during political negotiations, however, did not led to restitution of neither public law and order nor civilian concordance. Furthermore, situation becomes more and more unpredictable and may lead to the most critical impact for the present and the future of the Republic.}}\n\nAccording to ethnologist S.V.Chesko, nationalism is always connected to competition in areas for employment, material goods distribution, political rights and statuses and resources using, therefore during chaos in Chechnya many gangs and mobsters have captured commercial structures and industrial enterprises. Federal Government of Germany have provided aid for Chechnya expressed in education pioneer detachments of national armed forces<ref>Cheshko S.V. Role of ethnic nationalism during USSR collapse // Tragedy of the Great Power: national question and Soviet Union Collapse / ed. by G. N. Sevostyanov. Completed by S.M.Ishakov. - Moscow: Social and Political Thought, 2005. {{ISBN|5-902168-41-4}}, 2005. p. 448.</ref>.  In 2000 [[Rossiyskaya Gazeta]] published the general picture of events in Chechnya, paying attention to the facts of Russian-speaking people genocide:\n\n{{quotation|Almost total unemployment was in cities: men were walking with assault rifles, the law has disappeared, local armed squads ran rampant, their feuds were brutal. Fear, robberies, murders, kidnapping and slavery in streets of Grozny, beheading, drinking blood from glasses and public executions have conquered the city. Since 1990 the whole villages have been robbing the incoming trains, nowadays the railway connection has stopped. Bandit raids to Stavropol happened more often, the residents of suburbs were taken to slavery or as hostage, buses with passengers and helicopters were captured. The result was military intrusion of Chechens to Dagestan and terrorism acts in Russian cities. About 30 thousand of Russians in Chechnya were slaughtered, more than 200 thousand had to leave without apartments and property.<ref>[http://www.rg.ru/anons/arc_2000/0113/33.htm Rebuilding Chechnya, or why Ichkeriyan state failed] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191206130641/https://rg.ru/anons/arc_2000/0113/33.htm |date=2019-12-06 }} [[Rossiyskaya Gazeta]], 2000</ref>}}\n\n[[Security Council of Russia]] Secretary [[Ivan Rybkin]] (in 1996-1998) told about pre-war Grozny:\n{{quotation|There was anarchy in Chechnya. Russian city Grozny had really bad times. There was exodus of Russians, Tatars, Armenians and Jews caused by the pressure during this anarchy. They lost everything: apartments, cash, property, cars. It is necessary to say about hundreds of thousands people who left this biggest city of Northern Caucasus. I, as the State Duma Chariman, have got a letter directed to Boris Yeltsin and subscribed by 40 thousand people, where they expressed everything that happened in Chechnya. It was hard to read. My assistants come from those lands, from Terek \u2013 Nikolay Savchenko and Leonid Mayorov, stanitsas Kurskaya and Georgiyevskaya. They have brought this letter with tears in their eyes. [[Rossiyskaya Gazeta]] had published parts of this letter then.<ref>[http://echo.msk.ru/programs/razvorot/640337-echo/ 15th anniversary of Russian troops entering Chechnya] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191206130648/https://echo.msk.ru/programs/razvorot/640337-echo/ |date=2019-12-06 }}. [[Echo of Moscow]], Razvorot talk show, 11 December 2009</ref>}}\n\nAccording to human rights activists [[Memorial (society)|Memorial]], most of messages about human right abuses in Chechnya provided by Russian media were fake because Prosecutor and Ministry of Internal Affairs (MVD) have confirmed small part of those messages<ref>Russia\u2014 Chechnya: chain of mistakes and crimes; O.P.Orlov, A.V.Cherkasov for Memorial</ref>. [[Federal Counterintelligence Service]] did not accept any of applications with information on kidnappings or forced labor in Chechnya and did not conduct any operations or investigation, motivating that such questions are out of Service competence. Russian MVD and Prosecutor General officials stated that Russian and Chechen Internal Affairs Sections did not sign any agreements on functions distinction between two sides, so all crimes committed on Chechen territory had to be investigated by Chechnya law agencies<ref>[http://www.kommersant.ru/doc/73427 Chechnya denies fact of Russian slaves existing] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191206132043/https://www.kommersant.ru/doc/73427 |date=2019-12-06 }} Kommersant, No. 44 (512), 12 March 1994</ref>. However, there is an opinion, according to which all robberies and murders happened in a territory not controlled by any of the sides. The judge of Ramzes Goychaev case stated that the main reason for crime commiting was not xenophobia but defenseless of Russians<ref>[http://www.1tv.ru/news/crime/106941 First sentence in Pyatigorsk on the first criminal case on Russians genocide] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150215210915/http://www.1tv.ru/news/crime/106941 |date=2015-02-15 }} [[Channel One (Russia)|Channel One]], 18 April 2001</ref>: former Mayor of [[Kovrov]] Irina Tabatskova told that during Chechen Wars Russians were shot and thrown out of windows by Chechens, who wanted to capture their apartments<ref>[http://www.rus-obr.ru/ru-web/5974 Irina Tabatskova: Russians are not considered as people in Chechnya] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191206140826/http://www.rus-obr.ru/ru-web/5974 |date=2019-12-06 }} Russian Observer, 12 March 2010</ref>.\n\n=== Letter of Orthodox Christian Priest ===\nFather Zachary from Saint Michael the Archangel Church in Grozny has sent a letter to [[Alexiy II]]:\n{{quotation|It is impossible to describe by human words those horror life, which we live here. It is life in hell, between arrogant evil and total lawless: Chechens do not want to work peacefully together with people of other nations, they prefer to live by robberies, thefts, kidnapping. Most of them are armed, they take and rob everything they can, at home and during production. Slave trade has become typical in Chechnya, they make business of anything. And we, the Orthodox people, have to wait our destiny of slaves.<ref name=\"trudgenoc\" />}}\n\n== Human rights activists and publicity persons' opinion ==\nSome Russian human rights activists note that crimes against civilians on territories not controlled by Russian Armed Forces went unpunished<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20010702202213/http://www.hro.org/editions/karta/nr3031/chechnia.htm Chechnya: counter-terrorist operation or war?]</ref>. Also 1086 PACE Reslolution has condemned the capture of position near civilian settlements by Chechen armed detachments without preliminary warning of civilians on evacuation necessity. All similar crimes of illegal armed groups are included in books published by Memorial, however, authors state that the description of crimes by media is overblown<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.memo.ru/hr/hotpoints/chechen/itogi/index.htm |title=Human rights violation by Chechen Republic of Ichkeriya authorities |access-date=2019-12-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161215185306/http://www.memo.ru/hr/hotpoints/chechen/itogi/Index.htm |archive-date=2016-12-15 |url-status=live }}</ref>.\n\nRussian film director [[Stanislav Govorukhin]] explained the situation in Chechnya during meeting in State Duma on 17 March 1995:\n\n{{quotation|In August and September 1991, about 10 people were killed daily; then the amount reduced to 1\u20132, but it had been happening daily during 3 and half years. The Chechens were robbing, capturing apartments and making slogans: \"Do not buy flats of Vanya and Masha, soon the flats will eventually become yours\". Almost all Russian-speaking population has lost cars. I even do not want to tell how the Russians were bullied and humiliated. The only word that can describe this is \"genocide\". Nobody of human right defenders dared to move a muscle! Of course, I do not want to talk about that again because we talked too much about it. But if Sergey Adamovich Kovalev has screamed in his full own voice that human rights in Chechnya are smashed brutally, directing his message to the world, maybe we would have recovered much sooner and avoided tragedy. I met him twice during commission, and I asked him, \"Do you know anything about human rights violation during three years reign of Dudayev?\" - \"No\", he answered. Well, it is very strange. Moreover, I read today in cyphered messages cossacks' ataman Sharkov statement that in 1991 he had send Kovalyov printed documents and videos on genocide in Chechnya.}}\n\nGeneral Valery Baranov stated that \"sudden exodus of Russian-speaking people from Chechnya was caused by change of political powers and Dudayev's genocidal politics against Russian-speaking residents\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://vpk-news.ru/articles/4741 |title=From military actions to law enforcement functions |access-date=2019-12-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191206130730/https://vpk-news.ru/articles/4741 |archive-date=2019-12-06 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.vpk-news.ru/article.asp?pr_sign=archive.2006.120.articles.conception_01 |title=Baranov V. From military actions to law enforcement functions // Military Industry Courier, No. 4 (120). 1\u20147 February 2006 |access-date=6 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090318070418/http://www.vpk-news.ru/article.asp?pr_sign=archive.2006.120.articles.conception_01 |archive-date=18 March 2009 |url-status=dead }}</ref>. However, many public persons and publicists were denying facts of genocide of Russians made by Dudayev's regime. In 2009 [[Valeriya Novodvorskaya]] called the facts about genocide of Russians \"typical lie of Kremlin\". In 2012 she stated that no one Russian was killed in Chechnya, but mass migration took place because Russians did not understand Chechens, did not want to stay them because of their \"commies' mind\" and the genocide of Russians was caused by Russian Army actions<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://vnovodvorskaia.livejournal.com/947908.html#cutid1 |title=Genocide \u2013 Holocaust |access-date=2019-12-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170625105456/http://vnovodvorskaia.livejournal.com/947908.html#cutid1 |archive-date=2017-06-25 |url-status=live }}</ref>.\n\n{{quotation|That was all typical lie and Kremlin's fairy-tales which were told during [[First Chechen War]] and were going to assure that Russians were killed or expelled... I was there! First Deputy of Dudayev was Russian, his minister was Russian, first victims were old Russian people from five-stored houses \u2013 they refused to evacuate to Chechen villages. Russians bombed them firsts, they were first victims. So I cannot remember more arrogant lie than \"genocide of Russians in Chechnya\", even if we include [[Joseph Goebbels]]' propaganda.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://rutube.ru/tracks/3113020.html |title=Novodvorskaya statements on genocide in Chechnya |access-date=2019-12-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120311044021/http://rutube.ru/tracks/3113020.html |archive-date=2012-03-11 |url-status=live }}</ref>}}\n\n=== Appeal of former refugees to President of Russia ===\nIn 2005 a group of Russian refugees from Grozny sent an appeal to President of Russia and asked him to equal their rights with Chechens, to confirm fact of ethnic cleansing in Chechnya in 1991-1994, blaming Kremlin in trying not to reveal the facts of non-Chechen people persecutions and requiring for the same compensation as for returned ones to Chechnya. According to several sources, Chechen authorities have paid a huge compensation for those who returned to Chechnya.<ref name=\":12\" />\n\n=== Politicians and journalists' reaction ===\nIn July 2000 [[President of Russia]] [[Vladimir Putin]] said, \"Last years we saw large-scale genocide of Russian nation and Russian-speaking population in Chechnya. Unfortunately, nobody dared to move a muscle after that\"<ref>{{cite web  |url= http://kremlin.ru/events/president/transcripts/24166|title=Interview of Vladimir Putin|author=[[Marek Halter]]|work=[[Paris Match]]|date=2000-07-06|publisher=[[Kremlin.ru]]|accessdate=2015-08-17|lang=ru|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20150817204131/http://kremlin.ru/events/president/transcripts/24166|archivedate=2015-08-17}}</ref>. In 2002 Putin at the meeting with Chechen community representatives noted that [[Aslan Maskhadov]]'s reign led to genocide against other nations was arranged in Chechnya, total collapse of social and spiritual areas of life, economic collapse and hunger<ref>[http://www.mid.ru/bl.nsf/218603db65cac2d343256ac50038d63e/2723802722b3079143256c6e002a40e0?OpenDocument President of Russia Vladimir Putin at the meeting of Chechen community, 10 November 2002] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150215210115/http://www.mid.ru/bl.nsf/218603db65cac2d343256ac50038d63e/2723802722b3079143256c6e002a40e0?OpenDocument |date=15 February 2015 }} (Russian Ministry of Foreign Affairs)</ref>. In November 2000 [[Anna Politkovskaya]] had to answer the question on genocide of Russians in Chechnya, which was published in Novaya Gazeta<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://politkovskaya.novayagazeta.ru/pub/2000/2000-096.shtml |title=Anna Politkovskaya answers your questions |access-date=2019-12-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190523050045/http://politkovskaya.novayagazeta.ru/pub/2000/2000-096.shtml |archive-date=2019-05-23 |url-status=live }}</ref>:\n\n{{quotation|'''Kirill''': [...] Just one question: why cannot I remember any of your articles during 1991-1994 years when genocide of Russians was taking place in Chechnya?<br />\n'''Politkovskaya''': Dear Kirill! In 1991-1994 I did not have any physical opportunity to study the problem of Russians genocide in Chechnya. However, the genocide of Chechens nowadays is obvious, it is performed by military and the Chechens themselves. Many times I tried to explain myself many facts I witnessed, thinking of it as a regrettable case or the stupidity of the performer, but every time I failed, because there is a system of Chechen exterminating in Russia. I cannot explain the happening events in another way. Helas.}}\n\nRussian NTV channel journalist [[Yelena Masyuk]], who was captured by Chechens, in 2009 told that she had not seen any signs of Russians genocide, on which a lot of people were talking<ref>[http://echo.msk.ru/programs/albac/640854-echo/ Total Albatz show] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191206130652/https://echo.msk.ru/programs/albac/640854-echo/ |date=2019-12-06 }}, [[Echo of Moscow]], 13 December 2009</ref>. Her statements are disproved by another journalist, Timofey Borisov from [[Rossiyskaya Gazeta]], who mentioned many facts of genocide<ref>[http://www.rg.ru/anons/arc_2001/0905/1.shtm Dairy of a Chechen girl] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304222203/http://rg.ru/anons/arc_2001/0905/1.shtm |date=2016-03-04 }}, Timofey Borisov</ref>. M.K.Kokorin stated in the same newspaper that the list of assaults confirms official genocidal policy against Russians in Chechnya<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.rg.ru/anons/arc_2000/0401/4.htm |title=If we do not stop bandits in Chechnya, we will have to fight near our homes |access-date=2019-12-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191206130640/https://rg.ru/anons/arc_2000/0401/4.htm |archive-date=2019-12-06 |url-status=live }}</ref>, but publicist Leonid Radzihovsky said that there was not any inter-national conflict between Russians and Chechens because there was not any question on mass return of expelled Russians to houses captured by Chechens.<ref>[http://www.rg.ru/2008/08/05/radzihovskij.html Lobachevsky's diplomacy] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191206130644/https://rg.ru/2008/08/05/radzihovskij.html |date=2019-12-06 }} [[Rossiyskaya Gazeta]], No. 4721, 5 August 2008]</ref>\n\nYuri Shchekochikhin from Novaya Gazeta told once that there were serious contradictions on war perception between \"liberal journalistic\" and law enforcement agencies representatives<ref>[http://www.novayagazeta.ru/data/2001/45/00.html Covert operations and covert awards] ([https://web.archive.org/web/20100102060631/http://www.novayagazeta.ru/data/2001/45/00.html Archive])</ref>:\n\n{{quotation|And, furthermore! They were screaming at me as I was the only Russian journalist, \"Stop puking your lie all over us! Are we the guiltiest ones? Chechen are people, but who are we? Where were you with your human rights when there was total genocide of Russians in Chechnya?! Why did you not resent when Russians have to sell their houses for nothing?!\" I told them about robbed city, they answered, \"Why don't you write how 11 soldiers where hanged upside-down on the Council of Ministers building?\" I told them about Army Captain who had shot from assault rifle four civilians and thought they were guilty of deathes of all but six people from his battalion. They answered me about robbed property brought from trains to Chechen houses.}}\n\n[[Alfred Koch]] told during his lecture in [[Higher School of Economics]] that for unknown reasons nobody had told him that \"in fact, Russian-speaking population of Checheno-Ingushetia was partially slaughtered and partially expelled from territory, where they had been living for centuries\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://slon.ru/russia/gusinskiy_mne_pryamo_govoril_chto_esli_on_ne_polu-467005.xhtml |title=Businessman and ex-reformer Alfred Koch talking about privatization in Russia |access-date=2019-12-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304232707/http://slon.ru/russia/gusinskiy_mne_pryamo_govoril_chto_esli_on_ne_polu-467005.xhtml |archive-date=2016-03-04 |url-status=live }}</ref>. At the meeting of State Duma on 20 December 2006 Colonel [[Viktor Alksnis]] blamed Chechen authorities in double morale and told:\n\n{{quotation|I remind that from September 1991 to November 1994 (before first military clashes), according to media, more than 20 thousand Russian civilians, including women, elder people and children, were slaughtered in former Checheno-Ingush ASSR. Ethnic cleansing of Russian population was performed at its territory before first military actions, and more than 250 thousand Russians were expelled.}}\n\nDue to multiple Alksnis' statements on insufficient investigation of Russians genocide in Chechnya he was called by [[Investigative Committee of Russia]] in order to take the stand<ref>[http://www.newsru.com/russia/27jul2013/sledcomch.html Investigative Committee express interest in getting information on genocide of Russians in Chechnya] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191206130657/https://www.newsru.com/russia/27jul2013/sledcomch.html |date=2019-12-06 }} [[NEWSru.com]] on 27 July 2013</ref>. [[Doku Zavgayev]] noted that \"beheading began in Summer 1994, heads were publicly shown on squares, when there had been no Russian troops in the country and First Chechen War had not started yet\" and that ethnic cleansing was directed against multi-ethnic nation of Checheno-Ingush Republic and committed by illegal armed groups led by [[Zelimkhan Yandarbiyev]] and [[Aslan Maskhadov]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://transcript.duma.gov.ru/node/2895/ |title=Transcript of State Duma meeting, 2 October 1996 |access-date=6 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191206130634/http://transcript.duma.gov.ru/node/2895/ |archive-date=6 December 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>. In 2013 Russian journalist [[Maksim Shevchenko (journalist)|Maksim Shevchenko]] told that genocide of Russians was \"a legend which has not enough understandable proofs\" and that the first murders of Russians began after bombing Grozny<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.rusnovosti.ru/programms/prog/70601/271620/ |title=Russian News Service, 18:03-18:40 |access-date=2019-12-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141022112008/http://www.rusnovosti.ru/programms/prog/70601/271620/ |archive-date=2014-10-22 |url-status=dead }}</ref>. In the same year Sergey Popov told that genocide of Russians was happening from 1990 to 1994 (before the First Chechen War), when more than 200 thousand Russians ran away from the republic<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.stav.aif.ru/society/article/22196 |title=Sergey Popov on North Caucasus Federal District and ethnicity question |access-date=2019-12-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120206092504/http://www.stav.aif.ru/society/article/22196 |archive-date=2012-02-06 |url-status=live }}</ref>. [[Akhmed Zakayev]] denied any evidence confirming genocide of Russians in Chechnya of 1990s<ref>[https://meduza.io/feature/2014/12/11/posle-pervoy-voyny-my-proigrali-mir Akhmed Zakayev says, \"We have lost peace after the first war\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191206130631/https://meduza.io/feature/2014/12/11/posle-pervoy-voyny-my-proigrali-mir |date=2019-12-06 }} [[Meduza]], 11 December 2014, interview made by Ilya Azar</ref>. According to [[Sergey Stepashin]], White Book published in Russia is the main proof of Russian people genocide<ref>[http://teleskop-by.org/2018/09/04/sergej-stepashin-ya-ponimayu-pochemu-putin-vse-bolshe-i-bolshe-obrashhaetsya-k-bogu/ Sergey Stepashin, \"I understand why Putin is talking more and more to the God] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190517042139/http://teleskop-by.org/2018/09/04/sergej-stepashin-ya-ponimayu-pochemu-putin-vse-bolshe-i-bolshe-obrashhaetsya-k-bogu/ |date=2019-05-17 }} Teleskop, 4 September 2018</ref>.\n\n=== Russian Parliament members' reaction ===\nThe State Duma members had complicated and controversial opinion on genocide of non-Chechen people in Chechnya. [[Konstantin Borovoy]] denied all statements on genocide of Russians in Chechnya<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://rutube.ru/video/c9af7ed8934a0cbd66ee7b7edce01832/ |title=Borovoy and Novodvorskaya on genocide of Russians in 1990s |access-date=2019-12-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150215212748/http://rutube.ru/video/c9af7ed8934a0cbd66ee7b7edce01832/ |archive-date=2015-02-15 |url-status=dead }}</ref>, while former Department on Federation and Nations Affairs in State Duma [[Mikhail Burlakov]] insisted on the opposite point of view<ref>[http://www.pzrk.ru/genocide List of Burlakov's articles on genocide of Russians in Chechnya] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090405155050/http://pzrk.ru/genocide |date=2009-04-05 }} {{in lang|ru}}</ref>. For example, on 7 December 1994 Burlakov told that a law on defense of Russian population suffered from Chechen radical nationalists is necessary to be passed; Nikolay Lysenko noted that nobody interests what is happening to Russians in Chechnya.\n\n{{quotation|For some reason nobody asks: what is the situation of Russians in Chechnya? According to materials I have, Russians in Chechnya (at least in suburban and rural areas) have already become slaves in agricultural sphere.}}\n\nBurlakov offered to create Duma Committee on the situation with Russians in Chechnya, explaining that the problem of \"Russian slaves serving at plantations in Chechnya\" must be solved, but the results voting were against such Committee creating<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://transcript.duma.gov.ru/node/3126/ |title=Transcript of State Duma meeting, 7 December 1994 |access-date=6 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191206130630/http://transcript.duma.gov.ru/node/3126/ |archive-date=6 December 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>. Senator [[Evgeny Tarlo]] later compared situation [[War in Donbass|in Donbass]] and Chechnya, reminding that in Chechnya almost all Russians and Russian-speaking people were either killed or expelled\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://4pera.ru/news/picture_of_the_day/razgovor_s_ubiytsey/ |title=Talking to Murderer |access-date=2019-12-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170930083921/http://4pera.ru/news/picture_of_the_day/razgovor_s_ubiytsey/ |archive-date=2017-09-30 |url-status=dead }}</ref>.\n\n=== Writers as witnesses ===\nSeveral Russian writers who wrote on events in Chechnya were the direct witnesses of those events, however, their opinions distinguish. Some of writers denied any cases of discrimination of Russians. For example, Polina Zherebtsova, commenting statements on Russian troops entering Chechnya due to genocide of Russians, denied any facts of inter-national brawl:\n\n{{quotation|I was 9 years old in 1994. I understood very little of politics or relationships. I can just tell that the relationships between nations in Grozny and in the district, where my family lived, were peaceful and friendly. People talked nice and helped one another, I can't remember any ethnic feuds.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.krugozormagazine.com/show/Zherebtsova.1404.html|title=\u042d\u0442\u043e \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0443\u043f\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435. \u0413\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0440\u0438\u0442 \u043f\u0438\u0441\u0430\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0438\u0446\u0430 \u041f\u043e\u043b\u0438\u043d\u0430 \u0416\u0435\u0440\u0435\u0431\u0446\u043e\u0432\u0430, \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0435\u0436\u0438\u0432\u0448\u0430\u044f \u0432 \u0413\u0440\u043e\u0437\u043d\u043e\u043c \u0434\u0432\u0435 \u0432\u043e\u0439\u043d\u044b|trans-title=This is crime. A writer Polina Zherebtsova who survived two wars in Grozny speaks|author=\u0415\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0430 \u041c\u0430\u0433\u043b\u0435\u0432\u0430\u043d\u043d\u0430\u044f|date=2012-04-15|website=\u0418\u043d\u0442\u0435\u0440\u043d\u0435\u0442-\u0436\u0443\u0440\u043d\u0430\u043b \u00ab\u041a\u0440\u0443\u0433\u043e\u0437\u043e\u0440\u00bb|accessdate=2017-08-27|lang=ru|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170827170351/http://www.krugozormagazine.com/show/Zherebtsova.1404.html|archive-date=2017-08-27|url-status=live}}</ref>}}\n\nTV films director Igor Belyayev, who filmed 14 movies on Chechnya, supported the same version:\n{{quotation|All central newspapers depicted Dudayev as a monster and Grozny as bandits camp where any Russian appearing in the streets was torn apart. However, all of it was made 4 years before war when Grozny was still a peaceful city and Dudayev was the Soviet general. All this noise was made by press, but it is hard to say whether it was ordered or it was stupid mistake.<ref>{{cite book|author=Igor Belyayev|title=Documents spectacle. Revelations of television|trans-title=\u0421\u043f\u0435\u043a\u0442\u0430\u043a\u043b\u044c \u0434\u043e\u043a\u0443\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0442\u043e\u0432. \u041e\u0442\u043a\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f \u0442\u0435\u043b\u0435\u0432\u0438\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f|location=Moscow|publisher=Geleos|year=2005|page=[https://archive.org/details/spektakldokument0000beli/page/286 286]|isbn=5-8189-0403-2|url=https://archive.org/details/spektakldokument0000beli/page/286}}</ref>}}\n\nHowever, Yuri Kondratyev from Grozny states in his books, which won several awards (Teneta-2002, Memoirs Category) that Russians were people of \"second class\" in Chechnya<ref>[https://www.kp.ru/daily/23611/46725/ Russians of \"second class\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191206145130/https://www.kp.ru/daily/23611/46725/ |date=2019-12-06 }} [[Komsomolskaya Pravda]], 15 November 2005</ref>. He told about events of 1991 in Grozny in his book \"Grozny. Several days\":\n\n{{quotation|Krushchevka of my parents was in the center of the city at Partizanskaya St. against Republican Art Foundation. Once they saw a scene from the 4th floor of the building, a scene, which  became typical in the city. Several Russian guys were walking aside Art Foundation building when a black Volga passed and stopped near them. Several armed Chechens left Volga and shot the guys at point blank range from assault guns, then sat back at the car and slowly left the area. That was not mafia showdown, we had never had it. Then my parents understood the essence of \"independent Ichkeriya\". Both of them saw the war and fought, but this scene shocked them by its senseless brutality.}}\n\n== Number of victims evaluation ==\nIn July 1999 the Russian Ministry of Nations Affairs disclosed that during the years nine years since 1991, more than 21,000 Russian civilians{{Clarify|reason=When we say Russian civilians do we mean it in the verified by NGO civilians sense or the patriotic resistance civilian resistance type of Russian?|date=December 2019}} lost their lives. Property losses were estimated to be at least 100,000 domiciles destroyed or commandeered by native civilians. At least 46 thousand individuals had their property and passports confiscated.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ng.ru/regions/2003-05-23/4_kazak.html |title=Displacement of Russians in Chechnya is still going on due to federal officials' indifference |access-date=2009-08-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090531100704/http://www.ng.ru/regions/2003-05-23/4_kazak.html |archive-date=2009-05-31 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20010718065203/http://www.cdi.org/russia/johnson/3376.html Itar-Tass: Over 21,000 Russians Killed in Chechnya Since 1991] // Center for Defense Information</ref><ref>[http://www.vesti.ru/doc.html?id=16758 Vladimir Putin: Russia will not start negotiations with Chechen terrorists and bandits] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090318070746/http://www.vesti.ru/doc.html?id=16758 |date=2009-03-18 }} [[Russia-1|Rossiya Channel]], 19 December 2002</ref>.\n\nAccording to historic population data, there were 269,130 Russians in Checheno-Ingush ASSR in 1989 (24.8%) and there were 24,382 Russians in Chechen Republic of Russian Federation in 2010 (1.9%)<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ethno-kavkaz.narod.ru/rnchechenia.html |title=Chechnya population data |access-date=2019-12-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191013234204/http://www.ethno-kavkaz.narod.ru/rnchechenia.html |archive-date=2019-10-13 |url-status=live }}</ref>.\n\n== Accountability of perpetrators ==\nPutin's statement on human rights violations during counter-terrorism operations in the Northern Caucasus region of Russia pledged quick investigation into genocide in Chechnya cases and placed responsibility for these and other crimes on criminal \"Dudayev \u2013 Maskhadov regime\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.rg.ru/oficial/from_min/prezident/264.htm |title=Information provided by President of Russia Press Service |access-date=2019-12-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305013343/http://rg.ru/oficial/from_min/prezident/264.htm |archive-date=2016-03-05 |url-status=live }}</ref>. Despite multiple evidences of murders, robberies and other crimes committed by Chechen bandits, {{Citation needed|date=December 2019}}Russian law enforcement and justice agencies rarely tried to complete these cases. There was nohigh-profile cases or lawsuits against Chechen Republic of Ichkeriya authorities, the crimes committed by Ichkeriyan bandits were not investigated properly. Most of terrorists were killed during counter-terrorist operations. However, several noted lawyers expressed their opinion on non-Chechen population genocide: for example, Igor Kiselev, the former Acting Prosecutor of Chechen Republic and the official of Prosecutor General of Russia in the Northern Caucasus told Rossiyskaya Gazeta on the legitimacy and law and order in [[Chechen Republic of Ichkeriya]]<ref>[http://www.rg.ru/anons/arc_1999/1126/22.htm Blood feud is canceled] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090715082940/http://www.rg.ru/anons/arc_1999/1126/22.htm |date=2009-07-15 }} [[Rossiyskaya Gazeta]], 1999</ref>:\n\n{{quotation|Laws of self-described Ichkeriya and policy of her leaders lead to double standards. Outside we see almost European Constitution with guarantees of main rights and freedoms of a human and a civilian, rule of international law declaration, nice postulates on movement to common and fair world based on universal human values. Inside we see terrorist enclave where robberies, violence, slave trade and slave labor flourish, where drugs and counterfeit money production is taking place and where civilians of non-Chechen ethnicity are extinguished. Today somebody is worried by stream of refugees from Chechnya caused by military actions, but what should we do to mass emigration of Russians, Nogai people, Dargins, Avars and nations of Dagestan? During last years more than a half of Republic population and Russian citizens have left the republic, saving their lives and property.}}\n\nThe Criminal Code of Ichkeriya, which was published in Ichkeriya newspaper (6 September 1999) was the translation and copy of Republic of Sudan Criminal Code, according to experts: all the fines were fixed in Sudan pounds, paying for blood spilling was expressed in camels (100 camels for murder of a capable and free human)<ref>[http://www.bekkin.ru/index.php?rub=8&art=28 R. Bekkin, V. Bobrovnikov. Northern Caucasus is not a kingdom of noble outlaws] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181127152431/http://www.bekkin.ru/index.php?rub=8&art=28 |date=2018-11-27 }} // Tatarsky Mir, 2003, No. 19 (December). p.8]</ref>.\n\nOn 1 February 1995 a criminal case was opened by Prosecutor General of Russia against Dzhokhar Dudayev (Articles 64-A, 70-1, 133-1 part 1, 74 part 3 of Criminal Code of RSFSR). Dudayev was accused of inter-ethnic hatred:\n\n{{quotation|Due to policy conducted by D.M.Dudayev and his assistants in Chechen Republic the inter-social, inter-ethnic, inter-religious hatred and feud has appeared and led to the frank discrimination of Russian people, which are suffering from insults, reprisal threats, direct violence, degradation, illegitimate property confiscation and forced migration from republic. Dudayev's actions are related to part 3, Article 74 Criminal Code of RSFSR<ref name=\"white book\" />.}}\n\nHowever, Dudayev was killed on 21 April 1996 near Gekhi-Chu village (30 km from Grozny) by Russian secret services. In the end of 1999 the General Prosecutor of Russia ordered Aslan Maskhadov immediately visit Russian law enforcement agency and provide all information related on Russians genocide in Chechen Republic after finding mass graves in Chechnya<ref>[http://www.lenta.ru/vojna/1999/12/30/maskhadov/ Prosecutor General of Russia shall accuse Maskhadov of genocide of Russians in Chechnya] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160312221040/https://lenta.ru/vojna/1999/12/30/maskhadov/ |date=2016-03-12 }} {{in lang|ru}}</ref>. However, this case did not receive any public judicial reporting, Maskhadov did not appear to give information and was eventually killed on 8 March 2005 by FSB forces in Tolstoy-Yurt village (Grozny rural district), therefore investigation of crimes was not performed.\n\nFormer Mufti of Chechnya [[Akhmad Kadyrov]], who requires publicly to kill Russians in Chechnya, was later pardoned and was not held responsible for his calls to [[jihad]] against Russian. Later he was appointed as President of Chechnya by Vladimir Putin and killed on 9 May 2004. Next Day Putin signed a decree on Akhmad Kadyrov's name perpetuation in Grozny (naming the square in Grozny and school in Centoroy, where Kadyrov learned). President recommended to Moscow local authorities to think on the similar perpetuation in the capital, and 3 and a half months later one of the streets was renamed, despite locals' protests<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.kasparov.ru/material.php?id=47159C56D411F |title=Garry Kasparov says, \"Anna &#91;Politkovskaya&#93; proved that authorities and order did not cross at the same places in modern Russia |access-date=2019-12-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180723215458/http://www.kasparov.ru/material.php?id=47159C56D411F |archive-date=2018-07-23 |url-status=live }}</ref>. The appeal of public persons to Russian authorities with requiring to recognize legally the genocide of Russians in Chechnya was left without any reaction<ref name=Appeal/>.\n\n=== Ramzes Goychaev criminal case ===\nIn 2001 a Chechen person Ramzes Goychaev was initially accused by the court of Russians genocide in Chechnya in 1997-1999 (Article 357 of Russian Criminal Code). According to prosecution information, Goychaev's gang has murdered 10 Russian people in Chervlyonnaya (Shelkovsky District, Republic of Chechnya)<ref>[http://news.ng.ru/2001/04/18/987592126.html Chechen terrorist Goychaev sentenced to death] ([https://web.archive.org/web/20090531203613/http://news.ng.ru/2001/04/18/987592126.html Archive]) // [[Nezavisimaya gazeta]], 18 April 2001.</ref> Despite the fact that accusation of genocide was used for the first time in history of Russian justice, the court did not plead Goyachev guilty of genocide because of genocide understanding as \"the crime against world and humanity safety\"<ref>[http://www.kommersant.ru/doc.aspx?fromsearch=33b541f4-4ee9-4cf3-8276-ba78dd600e06&docsid=290776 Bandits were killing Russians] // Kommersant, \u2116 206 (2336), 10 November 2001] {{in lang|ru}}'</ref>. However, several murders were enough reason to sentence Goychaev to death penalty, which was finally replaced by [[life sentence]]<ref>[http://www.gazeta.ru/2001/04/18/pervyjsmertn.shtml The first death sentence for five years] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191031190749/https://www.gazeta.ru/2001/04/18/pervyjsmertn.shtml |date=2019-10-31 }} // [[Gazeta.Ru]], 18 April 2001 {{in lang|ru}}</ref>.\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Novye Aldi massacre]]\n* [[:ru:\u041f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u0430 \u0447\u0435\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0435\u043a\u0430 \u0432 \u0427\u0435\u0447\u043d\u0435 \u0432 \u0445\u043e\u0434\u0435 \u0412\u0442\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0439 \u0447\u0435\u0447\u0435\u043d\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u0432\u043e\u0439\u043d\u044b|Human rights during Second Chechen War]]\n* [[:ru:\u0420\u0443\u0441\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0435 \u0432 \u0427\u0435\u0447\u043d\u0435|Russians in Chechnya]]\n* [[Borozdinovskaya operation]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n== Literature ==\n* {{cite book|author=Romanov, P. V.|title=Chechnya. White Book|trans-title=\u0427\u0435\u0447\u043d\u044f. \u0411\u0435\u043b\u0430\u044f \u043a\u043d\u0438\u0433\u0430|url=https://archive.org/details/kgbivlast0000bobk|url-status=dead|location=Moscow|year=2000|publisher=[[RIA Novosti]], Rosinformcenter|isbn=5-900328-44-9|url-access=registration}}\n* {{cite book|author=Surkov A. P.|title=Chechnya in Flame of Separatism|trans-title=\u0427\u0435\u0447\u043d\u044f \u0432 \u043f\u043b\u0430\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0438 \u0441\u0435\u043f\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0442\u0438\u0437\u043c\u0430|url=http://www.lib.unn.ru/php/details.php?DocId=29469&DB=1|location=\u0421\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0442\u043e\u0432|publisher=Povolzhye academic state service publishing house|year=1998}}\n* {{cite book|author=Yuri Kondratyev|title=Grozny. Several days|trans-title=\u0413\u0440\u043e\u0437\u043d\u044b\u0439. \u041d\u0435\u0441\u043a\u043e\u043b\u044c\u043a\u043e \u0434\u043d\u0435\u0439|series=\u0412\u043e\u0441\u043f\u043e\u043c\u0438\u043d\u0430\u043d\u0438\u044f \u043e \u0413\u0440\u043e\u0437\u043d\u043e\u043c (Memory of Grozny)|url=http://conrad2001.narod.ru/russian/grozny.htm|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071215134142/http://conrad2001.narod.ru/russian/grozny.htm|url-status=dead|archive-date=2007-12-15}}\n* {{cite book|author=Dmitry Sokolov-Mitrich|title=Non-Tajik girls, non-Chechen boys|trans-title=\u041d\u0435\u0442\u0430\u0434\u0436\u0438\u043a\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0435 \u0434\u0435\u0432\u043e\u0447\u043a\u0438. \u041d\u0435\u0447\u0435\u0447\u0435\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0435 \u043c\u0430\u043b\u044c\u0447\u0438\u043a\u0438|publisher=Yauza-Press|year=2007|pages=320|isbn=978-5-903339-45-7}}\n* {{cite book|author=[[Paul Khlebnikov]]|title=Talking to Barbarian|trans-title=\u0420\u0430\u0437\u0433\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0440 \u0441 \u0432\u0430\u0440\u0432\u0430\u0440\u043e\u043c|pages=288|year=2005|publisher=Detective-Press|isbn=5-89935-057-1}}\n* {{cite journal|author=Vladimir Zykov|title=Blood and Dust|trans-title=\u041a\u0440\u043e\u0432\u044c \u0438 \u043f\u044b\u043b\u044c|editor=Introduction by Igor Shafarevich, \"The voice from total darkness|publisher=Nash Sovremennik|issue=11|year=1996|location=Moscow|lang=ru}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://reeed.ru/lib/books/dnevnik_mirnogo_zhitelya_goroda_groznogo/|title=\u00ab\u0414\u043d\u0435\u0432\u043d\u0438\u043a \u043c\u0438\u0440\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0436\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044f \u0433\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0434\u0430 \u0413\u0440\u043e\u0437\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e\u00bb \u0413\u0440\u0438\u0447\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0430 \u041d. \u0413.|trans-title=Diary of a Grozny Civilian N.G.Grichanov|date=2011}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://www.litsovet.ru/index.php/material.read?material_id=310875|title=\u00ab\u041d\u0430\u0441 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u0430\u043b\u0430 \u0420\u043e\u0434\u0438\u043d\u0430\u00bb|trans-title=We were betrayed by Motherland|date=2010|author=Konstantin Semenov}} (original name of book is \"Grozny Novel\" \u2014 \u00ab\u0413\u0440\u043e\u0437\u043d\u0435\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0440\u043e\u043c\u0430\u043d\u00bb)\n* {{cite web|url=http://www.litsovet.ru/index.php/material.read?material_id=368900|title=\u00ab\u0413\u0440\u043e\u0437\u043d\u0435\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0435 \u043c\u0438\u0440\u0430\u0436\u0438\u00bb|trans-title=Grozny Mirages|date=2011|author=Konstantin Semenov}}\n\n== Weblinks ==\n*{{cite web|url=https://www.refworld.org/docid/469f38d12.html| title=Chronology of events in Chechnya|publisher=Minorities at Risk| year=2004}}\n